1
00:00:53,295 --> 00:00:56,215
No,son. Never.

2
00:00:56,385 --> 00:00:59,005
The blood stays on the blade.

3
00:01:01,805 --> 00:01:04,225
One day you'll understand.

4
00:01:13,145 --> 00:01:15,485
Some of it I half remember.

5
00:01:16,065 --> 00:01:18,065
And the rest...

6
00:01:18,655 --> 00:01:21,365
The rest I took from dreams.

7
00:01:24,995 --> 00:01:28,415
St. Michael,the archangel, defend us in battle.

8
00:01:28,585 --> 00:01:33,165
Be our protector against the snares...

9
00:01:33,665 --> 00:01:36,925
...and the wickedness of the devil.

10
00:01:37,085 --> 00:01:38,885
Now,son,who's that?

11
00:01:39,045 --> 00:01:40,845
- St. Michael. - Who is it?

12
00:01:41,005 --> 00:01:42,925
- St. Michael! - And what did he do?

13
00:01:43,095 --> 00:01:45,885
He cast Satan out of paradise.

14
00:01:46,345 --> 00:01:48,225
Good boy.

15
00:02:58,505 --> 00:03:01,385
May God put the steel of the Holy Spirit in your spine...

16
00:03:01,545 --> 00:03:04,425
...and the love of the Blessed Virgin in your heart.

17
00:03:30,575 --> 00:03:33,915
- Hey,boyo! - Johnny.

18
00:03:34,085 --> 00:03:37,005
- What's the battle? - Natives against the Dead Rabbits.

19
00:03:37,165 --> 00:03:40,795
- Which are you? - What do you think? Dead Rabbits.

20
00:04:20,965 --> 00:04:23,335
Well,well,Monk.

21
00:04:23,545 --> 00:04:25,545
Are you with us or not?

22
00:04:25,715 --> 00:04:28,965
For the last time,Vallon, I'm with you if the money is right.

23
00:04:29,975 --> 00:04:32,885
I'll give you 10 per notch.

24
00:04:33,145 --> 00:04:36,765
- Ten? - You have my word.

25
00:04:40,985 --> 00:04:44,775
- Ten per notch? - Per new notch.

26
00:04:48,405 --> 00:04:50,245
Then I'm your man.

27
00:06:39,145 --> 00:06:41,975
Is this it,Priest? The pope's new army?

28
00:06:42,145 --> 00:06:45,525
A few crusty bitches and a handful of ragtags?

29
00:06:45,685 --> 00:06:49,235
Now,now,Bill,you swore this was a battle between warriors...

30
00:06:49,405 --> 00:06:51,735
...not a bunch of Miss Nancys.

31
00:06:51,905 --> 00:06:54,735
So warriors is what I brought.

32
00:06:57,655 --> 00:06:59,035
The O'Connell Guard.

33
00:06:59,245 --> 00:07:00,745
The Plug Uglies.

34
00:07:00,915 --> 00:07:03,375
The Shirt Tails.

35
00:07:08,255 --> 00:07:09,925
The Chichesters.

36
00:07:10,085 --> 00:07:12,885
The Forty Thieves.

37
00:07:29,065 --> 00:07:31,735
On my challenge...

38
00:07:31,945 --> 00:07:37,695
...by the ancient laws of combat, we have met at this chosen ground...

39
00:07:37,865 --> 00:07:40,285
...to settle,for good and all...

40
00:07:40,455 --> 00:07:44,415
...who holds sway over the Five Points:

41
00:07:44,745 --> 00:07:50,465
Us Natives,born right-wise to this fine land...

42
00:07:50,625 --> 00:07:53,425
...or the foreign hordes defiling it.

43
00:07:58,015 --> 00:08:03,185
By the ancient laws of combat,I accept the challenge of the so-called Natives.

44
00:08:03,355 --> 00:08:05,765
You plague our people at every turn.

45
00:08:05,935 --> 00:08:08,775
But from this day out, you shall plague us no more.

46
00:08:08,935 --> 00:08:12,735
For let it be known that the hand that tries to strike us from this land...

47
00:08:12,945 --> 00:08:14,615
...shall be swiftly cut down.

48
00:08:16,825 --> 00:08:20,285
Then may the Christian Lord guide my hand...

49
00:08:20,455 --> 00:08:22,705
...against your Roman popery!

50
00:08:22,865 --> 00:08:25,665
Prepare to receive the true Lord!

51
00:10:28,705 --> 00:10:30,625
Priest!

52
00:11:18,625 --> 00:11:21,085
Look to me.

53
00:11:22,425 --> 00:11:25,465
Who is this under my knife?

54
00:11:33,515 --> 00:11:35,975
Father,get up. Get up!

55
00:11:36,145 --> 00:11:39,775
Where are you? Where are you?

56
00:11:41,105 --> 00:11:42,615
Oh,my son.

57
00:11:45,945 --> 00:11:49,615
Don't never look away.

58
00:11:56,795 --> 00:11:59,465
Soon be over,Priest.

59
00:12:01,465 --> 00:12:03,465
Finish it.

60
00:12:21,485 --> 00:12:24,405
You may need this across the river.

61
00:12:33,325 --> 00:12:36,705
Ears and noses will be the trophies of the day.

62
00:12:37,585 --> 00:12:41,425
But no hand shall touch him!

63
00:12:43,505 --> 00:12:46,345
No hand shall touch him!

64
00:12:48,385 --> 00:12:51,015
He'll cross over whole...

65
00:12:52,015 --> 00:12:53,725
...in honor.

66
00:12:53,895 --> 00:12:56,605
Not before I get what's owed.

67
00:13:03,235 --> 00:13:05,195
No!

68
00:13:06,275 --> 00:13:10,785
It's fair. A touch indelicate,but fair.

69
00:13:15,415 --> 00:13:17,375
My sympathies.

70
00:13:18,335 --> 00:13:19,915
What will we do with the boy?

71
00:13:20,415 --> 00:13:22,545
Look at me.

72
00:13:28,255 --> 00:13:29,885
Give him to the law.

73
00:13:30,095 --> 00:13:32,765
See he gets a good education.

74
00:13:33,475 --> 00:13:36,435
Okay,boy,say goodbye to your father.

75
00:13:43,445 --> 00:13:45,695
- Get him! - Get him!

76
00:13:46,615 --> 00:13:48,065
Don't let him get away.

77
00:13:48,275 --> 00:13:50,735
Hurry,come in here!

78
00:13:52,945 --> 00:13:54,575
He's going downstairs.

79
00:14:10,965 --> 00:14:12,215
Come here,boy.

80
00:14:12,385 --> 00:14:15,265
- You're going to Hellgate,son. - There he is. Get him.

81
00:14:15,475 --> 00:14:18,475
- Priest Vallon died a noble death... - Let go of me!

82
00:14:18,645 --> 00:14:24,065
...but his Dead Rabbits is done and outlawed!

83
00:14:25,815 --> 00:14:30,905
Let no one even speak their name from this time on.

84
00:15:15,655 --> 00:15:21,035
In this place,you have grown from a boy into a man.

85
00:15:22,915 --> 00:15:26,625
Put to death the earthly things in you: Immorality,impurity...

86
00:15:26,795 --> 00:15:29,375
...passion,vengeance.

87
00:15:29,545 --> 00:15:32,885
The Lord has forgiven you.

88
00:15:33,045 --> 00:15:36,385
You also must forgive.

89
00:15:37,225 --> 00:15:39,845
You go forth to a country torn apart by civil strife.

90
00:15:42,225 --> 00:15:44,225
Thank you,Reverend.

91
00:15:47,315 --> 00:15:50,065
Lend your hand to the work that yet remains...

92
00:15:50,235 --> 00:15:52,485
...that this war may end...

93
00:15:52,655 --> 00:15:56,035
...and the plague of slavery that brought this conflagration...

94
00:15:56,195 --> 00:16:01,575
...down upon us vanish forever from the earth.

95
00:16:32,235 --> 00:16:34,155
In the second year of the Civil War...

96
00:16:34,315 --> 00:16:36,905
...when the Irish Brigade marched in the streets...

97
00:16:37,075 --> 00:16:40,075
...New York was a city full of tribes...

98
00:16:40,285 --> 00:16:43,625
...war chiefs,rich and poor.

99
00:16:43,785 --> 00:16:47,625
- Down with Lincoln! - Lincoln will make all white men slaves.

100
00:16:47,955 --> 00:16:49,455
It wasn't a city really.

101
00:16:51,295 --> 00:16:55,135
It was more a furnace where a city someday might be forged.

102
00:16:55,295 --> 00:16:56,965
That's the spirit,boys.

103
00:16:57,135 --> 00:17:01,475
- Go off and die for your blackie friends. - Down with the abolitionists!

104
00:17:01,635 --> 00:17:04,805
We should've run a better man against Lincoln when we had the chance.

105
00:17:04,975 --> 00:17:06,855
New York should secede from the Union!

106
00:17:07,015 --> 00:17:09,775
They trying to say we're no different than niggers?

107
00:17:09,935 --> 00:17:12,815
You ain't. Good evening,brother.

108
00:17:13,405 --> 00:17:15,275
- Praise the Union. - The Union forever!

109
00:17:15,445 --> 00:17:18,285
Go back to Africa,nigger!

110
00:17:18,735 --> 00:17:21,655
- Go back to Africa! - Leave him alone. We're free.

111
00:17:21,825 --> 00:17:24,955
The angriest talk was of the new Conscription Act...

112
00:17:25,125 --> 00:17:26,955
...the first draft in Union history.

113
00:17:39,965 --> 00:17:43,725
Join the Army,lads. Three square meals a day and good pay in your pocket.

114
00:17:43,885 --> 00:17:47,305
When the Irish came, the city was in a fever.

115
00:17:47,475 --> 00:17:52,065
Since the time of the great famine, they'd come streaming off the boats.

116
00:17:52,235 --> 00:17:53,985
And they got a right warm welcome.

117
00:17:54,145 --> 00:17:57,565
- Go back to Ireland,you dumb micks! - Remember that,you Irish gyps!

118
00:17:57,735 --> 00:17:59,655
Get back on the boat,Paddy!

119
00:18:00,325 --> 00:18:03,535
I only came two hours downriver from Hellgate.

120
00:18:03,705 --> 00:18:06,075
But they all took me for an immigrant.

121
00:18:06,245 --> 00:18:09,335
Why not? There were a thousand different accents in New York.

122
00:18:09,495 --> 00:18:14,215
And to the Natives,you see, we was all the same.

123
00:18:19,385 --> 00:18:22,845
Welcome to America,son. Your long,arduous journey is over.

124
00:18:23,055 --> 00:18:25,435
- Go back to your own country! - Vote Tammany!

125
00:18:33,395 --> 00:18:37,445
New York loved William Tweed and hated him.

126
00:18:37,605 --> 00:18:41,865
And those of us trying to be thieves, well,we couldn't help but admire him.

127
00:18:42,285 --> 00:18:45,535
Mr. Cutting,gentlemen, thank you for coming. It's an honor.

128
00:18:45,745 --> 00:18:47,615
Mr. Tweed.

129
00:18:49,705 --> 00:18:51,955
Sir,please. Excuse me.

130
00:18:52,295 --> 00:18:54,545
- I think you're frightening them. - So?

131
00:18:54,705 --> 00:18:58,425
Don't mind him. He used to be an Irishman.

132
00:18:59,925 --> 00:19:01,635
Ah,the Five Points.

133
00:19:01,925 --> 00:19:07,015
Murderers' Alley. Brickbat Mansion. The Gates of Hell.

134
00:19:07,185 --> 00:19:13,065
Here in this vile place. Look upon the face of this poor child.

135
00:19:13,225 --> 00:19:15,855
She lives in squalor...

136
00:19:16,025 --> 00:19:20,405
...in this godforsaken den of vice and misery behind me.

137
00:19:20,865 --> 00:19:23,285
Every year the reformers came.

138
00:19:23,445 --> 00:19:25,155
Every year the Points got worse...

139
00:19:27,495 --> 00:19:29,325
...as if it liked being dirty.

140
00:19:30,205 --> 00:19:33,545
- Where am I going to go? - The Reverend wants you out of here.

141
00:19:33,705 --> 00:19:35,915
You can't do this!

142
00:19:37,715 --> 00:19:41,175
A glorious resurrection will spring from the filthy depths...

143
00:19:41,335 --> 00:19:44,805
...to which these miserable creatures have fallen.

144
00:19:44,965 --> 00:19:47,675
In God,they will find their true home.

145
00:19:47,845 --> 00:19:51,475
You may or may not know,Bill, that every day I go to the waterfront...

146
00:19:51,645 --> 00:19:54,265
...with hot soup for the Irish as they come ashore.

147
00:19:54,475 --> 00:19:56,565
It's part of building a political base.

148
00:19:56,735 --> 00:19:59,645
I've noticed you there. You may have noticed me.

149
00:19:59,815 --> 00:20:03,065
Indeed I have. Throwing torrents of pavers and withering abuse...

150
00:20:03,235 --> 00:20:06,825
...on everyone stepping off those boats. - Lf only I had the guns...

151
00:20:06,995 --> 00:20:11,825
...l'd shoot each and every one of them before they set foot on American soil.

152
00:20:37,275 --> 00:20:39,775
Mulberry Street...

153
00:20:40,525 --> 00:20:42,275
...and Worth.

154
00:20:42,445 --> 00:20:47,155
Cross and Orange and Little Water.

155
00:20:47,365 --> 00:20:50,285
Each of the Five Points is a finger.

156
00:20:50,455 --> 00:20:54,785
When I close my hand, it becomes a fist.

157
00:20:54,955 --> 00:20:59,005
And any time that I wish, I can turn it against you.

158
00:20:59,205 --> 00:21:01,465
I know,but we're talking about different things.

159
00:21:01,625 --> 00:21:05,045
I'm talking about civic duty, responsibilities we owe to the people.

160
00:21:05,215 --> 00:21:08,135
Schools and hospitals, sewers and utilities.

161
00:21:08,305 --> 00:21:10,635
Street construction, repairs and sweeping.

162
00:21:10,805 --> 00:21:13,015
Business licenses,saloon licenses...

163
00:21:34,245 --> 00:21:38,745
St. Michael,the archangel, defend us in battle.

164
00:21:38,915 --> 00:21:42,755
Be our protector against the snares and the wickedness of the devil.

165
00:21:42,915 --> 00:21:45,545
Street cars,ferries,rubbish disposal.

166
00:21:45,755 --> 00:21:48,595
There's a power of money to be made in this city,Bill.

167
00:21:48,755 --> 00:21:52,845
With your help,the people must be made to understand...

168
00:21:53,015 --> 00:21:57,055
...that all these things are best kept within the Tammany family...

169
00:21:57,265 --> 00:21:59,435
...which is why I'm proposing an alliance...

170
00:21:59,645 --> 00:22:02,065
...between our two great organizations.

171
00:22:02,235 --> 00:22:06,565
- You're talking about muscle work. - That too. Muscle to match our spirit.

172
00:22:06,735 --> 00:22:10,735
- You own the crushers. Get them to do it. - The police? Oh,no. Jesus,no!

173
00:22:10,905 --> 00:22:14,745
The appearance of the law must be upheld...

174
00:22:14,915 --> 00:22:17,415
...especially while it's being broken.

175
00:22:28,795 --> 00:22:32,305
Give me the strength for what I must do.

176
00:22:35,345 --> 00:22:37,145
Who are you?

177
00:22:39,685 --> 00:22:41,565
- Hey! - No!

178
00:22:41,725 --> 00:22:44,985
I said,who are you? What are you doing here?

179
00:22:52,485 --> 00:22:55,455
I just like it down here is all.

180
00:22:56,155 --> 00:22:58,665
See what's in his pockets,Jimmy.

181
00:22:58,825 --> 00:23:02,335
- Look,boys,I really don't want a fight. - Don't want a fight?

182
00:23:02,495 --> 00:23:05,795
Don't worry,son, ain't gonna be much a fight.

183
00:23:12,965 --> 00:23:14,885
Don't kill me.

184
00:23:22,895 --> 00:23:24,895
Where'd you get that?

185
00:23:25,065 --> 00:23:27,485
I told you I didn't want a fight!

186
00:23:27,645 --> 00:23:30,315
Why not? Look how good you done.

187
00:23:37,745 --> 00:23:42,495
- You're the Priest's son,aren't you? - You,get away from me,understand?

188
00:23:42,665 --> 00:23:47,335
You don't remember me,do you? I's the one tried to help you.

189
00:23:49,085 --> 00:23:52,095
- What? - I's the one tried to help you...

190
00:23:52,255 --> 00:23:54,595
...when the Natives took you.

191
00:23:58,185 --> 00:24:03,185
- Oh,that was you? - Yeah. I thought you was killed.

192
00:24:05,895 --> 00:24:07,855
They just locked me up, you know that?

193
00:24:08,065 --> 00:24:10,025
This long?

194
00:24:10,235 --> 00:24:15,075
Well,I kept trying to escape,you know. They add on time for that.

195
00:24:16,115 --> 00:24:18,705
So,what are you doing back here?

196
00:24:19,405 --> 00:24:21,415
I guess I missed the place.

197
00:24:28,295 --> 00:24:30,045
Bowery Boys.

198
00:24:42,475 --> 00:24:43,935
Get back here!

199
00:24:44,105 --> 00:24:46,895
The Five Points,Paradise Square.

200
00:24:47,105 --> 00:24:50,145
The streets here are always lively of an evening.

201
00:24:51,145 --> 00:24:52,855
Who are the gangs around now?

202
00:24:53,025 --> 00:24:54,945
The Daybreak Boys and the Swamp Angels.

203
00:24:55,155 --> 00:24:57,325
They work the river,looting ships.

204
00:24:57,485 --> 00:25:00,205
The Frog Hollows shanghai sailors by the Bloody Angle.

205
00:25:00,365 --> 00:25:03,875
The Shirt Tails was rough, but they've become a bunch of dandies...

206
00:25:04,035 --> 00:25:06,955
...lolling around Murderers' Alley, looking like Chinamen.

207
00:25:07,205 --> 00:25:09,915
Hell-Cat Maggie,she tried to open her own grog shop.

208
00:25:10,085 --> 00:25:12,715
She drunk her own liquor and got throwed on the street.

209
00:25:12,875 --> 00:25:15,425
- Beautiful. - Now she's on the lay for anything.

210
00:25:15,595 --> 00:25:18,095
The Plug Uglies are from deep in the old country.

211
00:25:18,305 --> 00:25:20,555
Got their own language no one understands.

212
00:25:20,725 --> 00:25:24,095
They love to fight the cops. The Night Walkers of Ragpicker's Row.

213
00:25:24,555 --> 00:25:27,225
They work on their backs and kill with their hands.

214
00:25:27,395 --> 00:25:31,105
They're so scurvy only the Plug Uglies talk to them. But who understands them?

215
00:25:31,395 --> 00:25:33,815
The Slaughter Housers and the Broadway Twisters.

216
00:25:34,025 --> 00:25:37,155
They're a fine bunch of bingo boys. And the Little Forty Thieves.

217
00:25:37,325 --> 00:25:38,735
I used to run with them...

218
00:25:38,905 --> 00:25:41,825
...till they got took over by Bendrick the Cockroach.

219
00:25:41,995 --> 00:25:43,455
Bendrick carries a germ.

220
00:25:43,665 --> 00:25:46,585
If you try to leave the gang, he hacks up blood on you.

221
00:25:46,745 --> 00:25:50,125
The lime-juicers are nothing but a bunch of rapacious grab-ups.

222
00:25:50,915 --> 00:25:53,175
The True Blue Americans say they're a gang...

223
00:25:53,335 --> 00:25:56,135
...but all they do is stand on corners damning England.

224
00:25:56,295 --> 00:25:59,595
If you believe one word the British say,you're a fool.

225
00:25:59,765 --> 00:26:03,095
Do any of them got the sand of the Dead Rabbits?

226
00:26:06,725 --> 00:26:08,855
You don't say that name.

227
00:26:09,015 --> 00:26:13,695
That name died with your... They been outlawed.

228
00:26:14,195 --> 00:26:16,195
In the blockhouse, the Chinks told me...

229
00:26:16,355 --> 00:26:20,735
...that the Natives celebrate their victory every year. Is that true?

230
00:26:21,195 --> 00:26:23,785
Aye,that they do. It's quite the affair.

231
00:26:23,955 --> 00:26:26,825
The Butcher himself's got to invite you, or you don't go.

232
00:26:37,425 --> 00:26:40,345
Look where you're going,Johnny.

233
00:26:43,095 --> 00:26:45,885
You look stunned and poorly,sir.

234
00:26:50,225 --> 00:26:53,395
Quite a pair of conversationists, aren't you?

235
00:26:55,645 --> 00:26:59,235
Maybe not,but we're deep thinkers.

236
00:27:02,615 --> 00:27:08,745
Well,gentlemen,I leave you in the grace and favor of the Lord.

237
00:27:15,875 --> 00:27:18,545
Jenny,the finest bludget in all the Points.

238
00:27:18,715 --> 00:27:21,295
She is a prim-looking stargazer.

239
00:27:23,885 --> 00:27:26,265
But I'd check my pockets if I was you...

240
00:27:26,435 --> 00:27:29,725
...because I do believe she lifted your timepiece.

241
00:27:33,605 --> 00:27:36,105
Well,I let her take it.

242
00:27:36,315 --> 00:27:39,065
I let her take things all the time.

243
00:27:39,565 --> 00:27:42,115
- Is that right? - Yeah.

244
00:27:46,615 --> 00:27:49,075
We always liked a good fire in the Points.

245
00:27:50,285 --> 00:27:55,955
You could pick up a little swag. And if the cops came,you really got a show.

246
00:27:56,125 --> 00:27:59,585
The Municipal Police fought the Metropolitan Police.

247
00:27:59,755 --> 00:28:02,505
The Metropolitan Police, they fought the street gangs.

248
00:28:02,675 --> 00:28:05,095
Hurry up,men, before the Black Joke get there!

249
00:28:05,265 --> 00:28:08,975
There were 37 amateur fire brigades, and they all fought each other.

250
00:28:09,265 --> 00:28:15,105
The Black Joke are on their way,Tweed, and they'll beat the shite out of you.

251
00:28:17,435 --> 00:28:23,365
Okay,boys,get the hose out!

252
00:28:28,535 --> 00:28:31,115
It's the Black Joke!

253
00:28:31,285 --> 00:28:33,705
Go get them,boys!

254
00:28:34,455 --> 00:28:36,835
Give those Bowery Boys hell!

255
00:28:37,005 --> 00:28:40,625
- Quick,before there's nothing left. - Go back to the Bowery,you bums!

256
00:28:40,795 --> 00:28:43,635
Stop them. For God's sake, they're taking everything!

257
00:28:43,795 --> 00:28:46,555
In your next time of trouble, call on Tammany first.

258
00:28:46,715 --> 00:28:50,015
But it's not too late. You can still save my house.

259
00:28:50,725 --> 00:28:52,395
Let's go.

260
00:28:53,145 --> 00:28:56,065
I thought you said you was hungry.

261
00:28:59,485 --> 00:29:02,985
Grab what you can,Johnny. Let's get out of here.

262
00:29:03,695 --> 00:29:06,575
May I point out that this building is burning to ashes?

263
00:29:06,735 --> 00:29:11,075
May I point out this area is the province of my own Americus Fire Brigade...

264
00:29:11,245 --> 00:29:14,705
...and that you lot belong only in the Bowery?

265
00:29:15,875 --> 00:29:18,915
May I point out that you're outmanned, outmaneuvered...

266
00:29:19,085 --> 00:29:21,165
...and,in a moment,outfought?

267
00:29:21,375 --> 00:29:23,215
Am I?

268
00:29:29,055 --> 00:29:32,225
There's the Black Joke! Let's take them on the cobbles.

269
00:29:32,385 --> 00:29:36,765
Go spill some claret,boys. Go on,Shorty,have a nice muss.

270
00:29:36,935 --> 00:29:39,605
Clear the way for Bill the Butcher.

271
00:29:39,775 --> 00:29:41,895
Okay,boys,to work.

272
00:29:43,065 --> 00:29:46,775
What's the point? The fire's near burned anything of value inside.

273
00:29:46,945 --> 00:29:50,245
Boys,forget that one. Next building over.

274
00:29:50,405 --> 00:29:53,245
Mustn't let it spread. Take what you want from that one.

275
00:29:53,415 --> 00:29:54,455
What are you doing?

276
00:29:54,615 --> 00:29:57,415
There's nothing wrong with this one. This is my house.

277
00:30:01,255 --> 00:30:02,715
- Johnny! - Help!

278
00:30:02,875 --> 00:30:05,385
- Johnny! - Help!

279
00:30:06,755 --> 00:30:09,595
Help! Help!

280
00:30:13,555 --> 00:30:15,345
Help!

281
00:30:19,265 --> 00:30:21,485
Come on. Come on,Johnny,get up.

282
00:30:21,935 --> 00:30:23,855
Leave that!

283
00:30:31,155 --> 00:30:32,575
You two,out of the way!

284
00:30:49,965 --> 00:30:52,135
His name's Amsterdam.

285
00:30:54,635 --> 00:30:57,645
- How's the beak? - Ain't so bad.

286
00:30:57,805 --> 00:31:01,935
You. You got anything, you give it up or you get out.

287
00:31:13,155 --> 00:31:14,995
Is that it?

288
00:31:15,405 --> 00:31:17,415
That's it.

289
00:31:18,875 --> 00:31:22,165
Right. Here's the rake. Everything comes here. We fence it.

290
00:31:22,375 --> 00:31:25,795
Johnny takes our tribute to the Natives, and we chop up the winnings...

291
00:31:26,005 --> 00:31:29,465
...each to his equal portion, amongst the gang.

292
00:31:29,675 --> 00:31:33,135
Does that meet with your approval,Hellgate?

293
00:31:33,345 --> 00:31:34,975
My approval?

294
00:31:35,135 --> 00:31:38,015
What's the matter,Jack Sprat? Can't think for yourself?

295
00:31:39,725 --> 00:31:42,645
- I'll slit your fucking throat! - Hey,come on!

296
00:31:42,855 --> 00:31:44,065
Hey!

297
00:31:47,525 --> 00:31:51,575
You boys will settle with me before settling with each other.

298
00:31:54,995 --> 00:31:57,705
I come for my due and proper.

299
00:32:16,675 --> 00:32:18,845
Well,this ain't a bad haul.

300
00:32:19,345 --> 00:32:22,855
When folks start in to saying to where the country is going to hell...

301
00:32:23,055 --> 00:32:26,025
...I always tell them, "You just look at all the hard work...

302
00:32:26,185 --> 00:32:29,565
...our fine young lads is doing down in the Five Points."

303
00:32:29,775 --> 00:32:33,825
Oh,yeah. Now this is just the thing for Mrs. Mulraney.

304
00:32:33,985 --> 00:32:36,325
All right there,Happy Jack, leave us something...

305
00:32:36,495 --> 00:32:38,865
...to quarter to Bill the Butcher,eh?

306
00:32:39,035 --> 00:32:40,575
Would you?

307
00:32:52,175 --> 00:32:54,755
Not my favorite tune.

308
00:33:01,975 --> 00:33:04,225
Thank you,boys.

309
00:33:04,765 --> 00:33:07,725
You keep out of trouble now.

310
00:33:25,835 --> 00:33:29,915
Every year the Natives celebrated the killing of my father all over again...

311
00:33:31,585 --> 00:33:36,675
...at Sparrow's Chinese Pagoda in Mott Street.

312
00:33:36,845 --> 00:33:40,475
The Chinks hated the Natives worse than we did.

313
00:33:43,345 --> 00:33:47,685
The drum rolls,and the Butcher drinks a glass of fire.

314
00:33:51,815 --> 00:33:54,235
When you kill a king...

315
00:33:54,775 --> 00:33:57,735
...you don't stab him in the dark.

316
00:33:59,155 --> 00:34:04,415
You kill him where the whole court can watch him die.

317
00:34:08,335 --> 00:34:10,835
Hey,you got any timber?

318
00:34:20,345 --> 00:34:23,935
As I walked down to Chatham Street A fair maid I did meet

319
00:34:24,095 --> 00:34:27,475
She asked me to see her home She lived in Bleeker Street

320
00:34:27,645 --> 00:34:31,735
To me a-weigh,you Santee My dear Annie

321
00:34:31,895 --> 00:34:35,195
Oh,you New York girls Can't you dance the polka?

322
00:34:35,355 --> 00:34:39,275
To me a-weigh,you Santee My dear Annie

323
00:34:39,445 --> 00:34:42,995
Oh,you New York girls Can't you dance the polka?

324
00:34:43,205 --> 00:34:46,495
When we got to Bleeker Street We stopped at 44

325
00:34:46,705 --> 00:34:50,165
Her mother and her sister Dared to meet us at the door

326
00:35:00,845 --> 00:35:04,675
- Hey,Maggie. Right ear or left ear? - Give us a drink,you idiot.

327
00:35:04,845 --> 00:35:06,475
Help yourself.

328
00:35:06,645 --> 00:35:08,515
- Final bets! - To health.

329
00:35:08,685 --> 00:35:11,725
Place your bets. Betting closes in two minutes.

330
00:35:11,895 --> 00:35:13,235
Place your bets.

331
00:35:13,395 --> 00:35:17,525
Gentlemen,the match is due to commence.

332
00:35:17,735 --> 00:35:21,235
The count to beat is 25 rodents in three minutes.

333
00:35:21,405 --> 00:35:23,745
Towser against the vermin.

334
00:35:23,905 --> 00:35:25,575
- Are the enumerators satisfied? - Fifty!

335
00:35:25,785 --> 00:35:27,865
- Yes! - Let them go!

336
00:35:41,755 --> 00:35:44,885
- Where you going,boy? - I'm here to pay tribute to Bill.

337
00:35:45,055 --> 00:35:47,475
Are you now? Give it to me. I'll give it to him.

338
00:35:47,635 --> 00:35:50,435
No,thanks. I'll give it to him myself.

339
00:35:52,065 --> 00:35:54,565
What do you want to keep, the money or your teeth?

340
00:35:54,725 --> 00:35:56,395
John.

341
00:35:57,315 --> 00:35:58,985
Welcome.

342
00:36:06,825 --> 00:36:09,455
From me and me lads,sir.

343
00:36:16,125 --> 00:36:19,425
Mate of yours? Where's he from?

344
00:36:20,045 --> 00:36:22,295
Oh,he's not from here,sir.

345
00:36:24,965 --> 00:36:26,725
You.

346
00:36:44,025 --> 00:36:46,285
That's close enough.

347
00:36:57,295 --> 00:37:01,885
Your friend can't look me in the eye. That's not an admirable characteristic.

348
00:37:02,045 --> 00:37:05,965
No one can look you in the eye,Bill. Not when you're playing cards.

349
00:37:24,525 --> 00:37:28,195
This is whist. It's a gentleman's game. Make a gentleman's bet.

350
00:37:28,615 --> 00:37:32,825
- I'm betting large,Bill. - That ain't large.

351
00:37:41,335 --> 00:37:44,505
Please,don't make that noise again, Harvey.

352
00:37:46,885 --> 00:37:50,345
I like a man who's willing to burn for his swag.

353
00:37:53,725 --> 00:37:56,395
How do you fare on water? Come closer.

354
00:37:56,565 --> 00:37:59,855
Close,John. I ain't gonna bite. Close.

355
00:38:03,195 --> 00:38:07,235
There's a Portuguese ship lying low in the harbor,quarantined three weeks.

356
00:38:07,405 --> 00:38:09,615
Get there before the Daybreak Boys strip her...

357
00:38:09,785 --> 00:38:11,405
...maybe you and me will talk more.

358
00:38:11,575 --> 00:38:14,165
- Consider it done,sir. - Good boy.

359
00:38:15,285 --> 00:38:18,955
And you,whatever your name is... What is your name?

360
00:38:22,585 --> 00:38:29,005
- Amsterdam,sir. - Amsterdam. I'm New York.

361
00:38:29,215 --> 00:38:31,725
Don't you never come in here empty-handed again.

362
00:38:31,925 --> 00:38:35,265
You gotta pay for the pleasure of my company.

363
00:38:35,475 --> 00:38:37,395
Take him for a boat ride,John.

364
00:38:37,555 --> 00:38:40,685
Who knows,but he might save your life again.

365
00:38:44,315 --> 00:38:47,065
The Daybreak Boys catch us, they'll slit our throats.

366
00:38:47,275 --> 00:38:49,945
I'll do it myself in a minute if you don't keep quiet.

367
00:38:50,155 --> 00:38:53,285
I never liked the harbor after dark.

368
00:38:53,455 --> 00:38:56,875
And now each night they brung ashore the bodies of the soldiers.

369
00:38:57,035 --> 00:38:58,915
Many mothers have not even the solace...

370
00:38:59,125 --> 00:39:01,505
...of knowing where their sons have fallen.

371
00:39:01,665 --> 00:39:04,375
I lost my own eldest at Antietam.

372
00:39:04,545 --> 00:39:07,135
His mother and I were unable to recover his remains.

373
00:39:07,295 --> 00:39:10,055
- It was a mournful sight. - The war can't last forever.

374
00:39:10,215 --> 00:39:12,925
But we had business of our own.

375
00:39:21,645 --> 00:39:26,605
The Daybreak Boys have been here, and there's nothing left. Let's go back.

376
00:39:30,275 --> 00:39:32,785
What the hell?

377
00:39:39,665 --> 00:39:41,795
Jimmy,get down!

378
00:39:44,005 --> 00:39:47,835
Jesus,that'll bring the harbor cops for sure. Fuck off.

379
00:39:55,555 --> 00:39:57,635
Let's take a look.

380
00:40:00,395 --> 00:40:02,725
Jesus,they killed everybody.

381
00:40:02,895 --> 00:40:05,735
There's nothing here but a bunch of dead sea-crabs.

382
00:40:05,895 --> 00:40:08,195
Come on,let's go.

383
00:40:09,775 --> 00:40:12,195
- Shove off. - No,wait for Amsterdam.

384
00:40:12,405 --> 00:40:14,575
Where's Amsterdam?

385
00:40:17,035 --> 00:40:19,575
- No,you damn fool,take him! - What in the hell for?!

386
00:40:19,745 --> 00:40:21,835
Look in my glims. I said no less than 15.

387
00:40:22,035 --> 00:40:25,375
- Is this fresh? - Four hours most.

388
00:40:25,705 --> 00:40:28,335
Much obliged,gents.

389
00:40:35,385 --> 00:40:37,515
What's that word?

390
00:40:38,385 --> 00:40:40,725
- It means body snatchers. - I didn't ask the meaning.

391
00:40:40,895 --> 00:40:42,265
I asked the word.

392
00:40:42,935 --> 00:40:44,395
Ghoul.

393
00:40:45,975 --> 00:40:49,395
Ghoul? That's a good word.

394
00:40:49,565 --> 00:40:55,865
"Ghoul Gang Slaughters. A Fresh Outrage in the Five Points."

395
00:40:56,075 --> 00:40:58,535
- That's a notice you can be proud of. - Thank you.

396
00:40:58,705 --> 00:41:02,455
A low thing,to do that to a body. Low.

397
00:41:02,625 --> 00:41:04,915
Why? They could have left that ship with nothing.

398
00:41:05,085 --> 00:41:09,255
Instead they made The Police Gazette, a periodical of note.

399
00:41:09,415 --> 00:41:11,835
A body's supposed to stay beneath the earth...

400
00:41:12,005 --> 00:41:15,175
...wearing a wooden coat until the Resurrection.

401
00:41:15,345 --> 00:41:18,265
These two are a pair of sons of Irish bitches,same as you.

402
00:41:18,425 --> 00:41:20,515
It don't seem to bother them none.

403
00:41:20,685 --> 00:41:23,605
But then maybe they don't share your religious scruples.

404
00:41:23,765 --> 00:41:26,565
Maybe they're just a couple of Fidlam Bens.

405
00:41:32,155 --> 00:41:36,115
I've been called a lot of things,mister, but I ain't never been called...

406
00:41:36,275 --> 00:41:39,995
- Fidlam Bens. - Fidlam Bens. Right.

407
00:41:40,155 --> 00:41:46,545
Well,if I knew what in the hell that meant,I'd be inclined to take offense.

408
00:41:46,705 --> 00:41:50,915
A Fidlam Bens is a fellow who steals anything,dead or alive...

409
00:41:51,125 --> 00:41:54,175
...because he's too low to work up a decent lay for himself.

410
00:41:54,335 --> 00:41:56,635
Count that careful,Bill. Count that careful.

411
00:41:56,805 --> 00:41:59,845
- I'm telling you,that's all there is... - Now,chiseler...

412
00:42:00,015 --> 00:42:03,555
If you'd said "chiseler," now there's a word I understand. You know?

413
00:42:03,725 --> 00:42:07,855
- Now,is that what you're calling us? - I can think of many things to call you.

414
00:42:08,015 --> 00:42:11,315
Right. But I asked if you was calling us chiselers.

415
00:42:11,485 --> 00:42:14,235
Supposing I am?

416
00:42:16,195 --> 00:42:18,865
Well,then we got business.

417
00:42:19,695 --> 00:42:22,075
That we do.

418
00:42:28,875 --> 00:42:31,835
- A fight! There's a fight! - Two bucks on McGloin.

419
00:42:32,005 --> 00:42:34,465
- Four bits on the kid. - Five bits on the kid.

420
00:42:34,625 --> 00:42:37,465
I got two on Amsterdam.

421
00:42:45,975 --> 00:42:49,355
Come on,McGloin,he's just a kid.

422
00:42:49,975 --> 00:42:52,525
Four bits to back Amsterdam.

423
00:42:59,235 --> 00:43:02,155
Watch his left,McGloin. Watch his left.

424
00:43:41,695 --> 00:43:44,865
- All right,that'll do. That'll do. - Anything to say now,huh?!

425
00:43:45,075 --> 00:43:47,705
That'll do,for chrissake. Drag him off.

426
00:43:47,865 --> 00:43:51,035
- That's enough,kid. - You got him. Come on,kid,you won.

427
00:43:51,205 --> 00:43:54,045
McGloin. He's a kid too,McGloin.

428
00:43:54,205 --> 00:43:56,795
You're getting too old for it,McGloin.

429
00:44:18,355 --> 00:44:23,785
McGloin,how would that head look without the ears and the nose on it?

430
00:44:25,075 --> 00:44:27,455
You'd better leave that head alone,Bill.

431
00:44:27,615 --> 00:44:31,165
I think I'm gonna trim the ears and the beak off of that head.

432
00:44:32,495 --> 00:44:34,665
Make a nice pot of soup of that head.

433
00:44:34,835 --> 00:44:37,585
You could find a tastier head than that,Bill.

434
00:44:37,755 --> 00:44:41,135
I ain't got the stomach for no Irish stew.

435
00:44:43,555 --> 00:44:48,685
The mighty McGloin almost fishhooked by a sprat.

436
00:44:57,355 --> 00:45:01,485
On the seventh day,the Lord rested, but before that he did...

437
00:45:01,655 --> 00:45:07,575
...he squatted over the side of England, and what came out of him was Ireland.

438
00:45:07,745 --> 00:45:11,745
- No offense,son. - Oh,none taken,sir. I grew up here.

439
00:45:11,955 --> 00:45:16,455
All I ever knew of Ireland was in the talk of the others at the orphan asylum.

440
00:45:16,665 --> 00:45:21,635
In which part of that excrementitious isle were your forebears spawned?

441
00:45:21,795 --> 00:45:27,425
I've been told Kerry,but I lost proof of it in my language at the asylum.

442
00:45:27,595 --> 00:45:30,845
I was raised in a very similar establishment myself.

443
00:45:31,015 --> 00:45:34,475
Now everything you see belongs to me, to one degree or another.

444
00:45:34,645 --> 00:45:37,725
The beggars and newsboys and quick thieves here in Paradise.

445
00:45:37,895 --> 00:45:41,445
The sailor dives and gin mills and blind tigers on the waterfront.

446
00:45:41,605 --> 00:45:44,565
The anglers and amusers, the she-hes and the Chinks.

447
00:45:44,735 --> 00:45:46,535
Everybody owes,everybody pays...

448
00:45:46,695 --> 00:45:52,615
...because that's how you stand up against the rising of the tide.

449
00:45:52,785 --> 00:45:55,995
- Is that right,boys? - Yeah,Bill. That's right.

450
00:45:56,205 --> 00:46:02,005
Enlist. Join up. Serve your country. Come on in out of the draft,boys.

451
00:46:02,175 --> 00:46:04,425
Volunteer and get your $50 bonus.

452
00:46:06,295 --> 00:46:10,555
We need 30,000 volunteers,and we're prepared to pay $677 per volunteer.

453
00:46:10,725 --> 00:46:13,095
- Please read this. Thank you. - Thanks.

454
00:46:13,265 --> 00:46:15,685
Would you like to take one of these to fill out?

455
00:46:15,895 --> 00:46:19,435
Three square meals a day. Three square meals a day.

456
00:46:19,605 --> 00:46:22,355
Young man,enlist and serve your country.

457
00:46:22,565 --> 00:46:24,525
Three square meals a day,gentlemen.

458
00:46:24,695 --> 00:46:27,365
If you're interested, read this and consider joining.

459
00:46:27,525 --> 00:46:30,365
Everywhere you went people talked about the draft.

460
00:46:30,535 --> 00:46:33,745
Now,you could buy your way out for $300...

461
00:46:33,915 --> 00:46:35,995
...but who had $300?

462
00:46:36,165 --> 00:46:38,915
For us it might as well have been 3,000,000.

463
00:46:39,125 --> 00:46:43,085
The recruiters? They was too scared of the gangs to come after us.

464
00:46:43,295 --> 00:46:48,135
Besides,we never dreamt the war would ever touch New York.

465
00:46:48,305 --> 00:46:49,715
Good morning,sir.

466
00:46:51,675 --> 00:46:53,095
You!

467
00:46:53,595 --> 00:46:55,265
Don't you run into me.

468
00:46:56,645 --> 00:46:58,395
Fair enough.

469
00:47:03,195 --> 00:47:05,275
I said,don't run into me!

470
00:47:05,445 --> 00:47:07,615
Well,sorry.

471
00:47:13,455 --> 00:47:16,825
- Everything in place? - It seems so.

472
00:47:16,995 --> 00:47:19,915
Well,then I leave you in the grace and favor of the Lord.

473
00:47:20,125 --> 00:47:22,255
- Thank you. - That's right.

474
00:47:29,845 --> 00:47:33,135
Oh,the dirty mab!

475
00:47:36,805 --> 00:47:38,435
Oh,no.

476
00:47:38,605 --> 00:47:41,065
- I'm sorry. - Allow me.

477
00:47:43,355 --> 00:47:46,815
- Thank you kindly,sir. - Oh,it's my pleasure.

478
00:47:47,605 --> 00:47:49,775
I hope you won't think me rude if I speak.

479
00:47:49,985 --> 00:47:52,155
I wouldn't want to appear forward.

480
00:47:52,325 --> 00:47:57,165
Well,sir,that depends on what you say.

481
00:48:05,125 --> 00:48:09,505
Would you call me reckless if I said you were the prettiest girl in New York?

482
00:48:09,715 --> 00:48:12,425
Only New York?

483
00:48:14,265 --> 00:48:15,475
This is my stop.

484
00:48:17,635 --> 00:48:20,645
May I walk with you a little then?

485
00:48:20,805 --> 00:48:23,525
That,sir,would be too bold.

486
00:48:41,205 --> 00:48:42,335
Good morning.

487
00:48:50,715 --> 00:48:54,215
For every lay we had a different name.

488
00:48:54,385 --> 00:48:56,675
An "angler" put a hook on the end of a stick...

489
00:48:56,885 --> 00:49:00,015
...to drop behind store windows and doors.

490
00:49:00,185 --> 00:49:03,725
An "autumn diver" picked your pocket in church.

491
00:49:03,895 --> 00:49:06,485
A "badger" gets a fellow into bed with a girl...

492
00:49:06,645 --> 00:49:09,565
...then robs his pockets while they're on the go.

493
00:49:10,105 --> 00:49:13,865
Jenny was a "bludget," a girl pickpocket...

494
00:49:14,025 --> 00:49:17,945
...and a "turtledove."

495
00:49:19,615 --> 00:49:22,825
A turtledove goes uptown dressed like a housemaid...

496
00:49:22,995 --> 00:49:26,705
...picks out a fine house and goes right through the back door.

497
00:49:27,165 --> 00:49:28,415
Robs you blind.

498
00:49:30,425 --> 00:49:33,715
It takes a lot of sand to be a turtledove.

499
00:49:55,825 --> 00:49:59,785
I'll have my medal back. Oh,Jesus!

500
00:50:06,375 --> 00:50:08,375
Don't do that again.

501
00:50:08,545 --> 00:50:11,375
Listen! I said,don't do that...

502
00:50:12,045 --> 00:50:14,175
Go back to the Points and leave me to my business...

503
00:50:14,335 --> 00:50:17,305
...or I will open your throat, so help me God.

504
00:50:20,635 --> 00:50:22,595
All right.

505
00:50:24,145 --> 00:50:26,145
Go on then.

506
00:50:28,315 --> 00:50:30,275
I would.

507
00:50:31,815 --> 00:50:33,155
Go on then.

508
00:50:55,465 --> 00:50:58,175
Now give me back my medal.

509
00:50:58,505 --> 00:51:00,805
Make it quick!

510
00:51:07,935 --> 00:51:10,855
I don't know which one's yours.

511
00:51:17,485 --> 00:51:19,865
Suppose I help myself to everything?

512
00:51:22,655 --> 00:51:24,405
Suppose you do.

513
00:52:03,575 --> 00:52:06,365
May I walk with you a little then?

514
00:52:14,915 --> 00:52:17,585
What do you suppose a fellow could earn here in a day?

515
00:52:17,925 --> 00:52:21,095
- Maybe we could pal in together. - Oh,I think you're a bit...

516
00:52:21,255 --> 00:52:25,885
...rough for this sort of game. Besides,I work alone.

517
00:52:26,095 --> 00:52:29,015
Alone? Well,what do you quarter to the Butcher?

518
00:52:29,185 --> 00:52:31,435
- Me? Nothing. - Nothing?

519
00:52:31,605 --> 00:52:34,145
The Butcher and me have a special arrangement.

520
00:52:41,615 --> 00:52:45,405
- I don't want to see you again. - Well,I don't blame you.

521
00:52:46,115 --> 00:52:48,995
Pennies in their pockets and hope in their eyes...

522
00:52:49,165 --> 00:52:51,205
...they peer to the west...

523
00:52:51,415 --> 00:52:55,955
...searching the horizon for a glimpse of land and salvation.

524
00:52:57,795 --> 00:52:59,375
A glimpse of America.

525
00:52:59,545 --> 00:53:02,885
Seeing all this poverty must be most unsettling,Miss Schermerhorn.

526
00:53:03,045 --> 00:53:06,635
Some days,of course, the uptown gangs come down to us.

527
00:53:07,265 --> 00:53:10,935
The Schermerhorns was one of the oldest families in New York.

528
00:53:11,095 --> 00:53:12,645
They didn't run the city...

529
00:53:12,805 --> 00:53:15,275
...but they was listened to carefully by them that did.

530
00:53:15,435 --> 00:53:17,235
Commissioner Brunt said you wished to view...

531
00:53:17,395 --> 00:53:19,775
...the Points in all its splendor and squalor.

532
00:53:19,945 --> 00:53:22,195
"Spare nothing concerning the conditions," said he.

533
00:53:22,365 --> 00:53:25,285
Yeah,nothing except our safety,constable.

534
00:53:25,445 --> 00:53:29,035
I'm sure we can be in no danger while we're in the constable's company.

535
00:53:29,205 --> 00:53:32,785
Quite so,madam. Witness.

536
00:53:39,925 --> 00:53:43,045
- Shall we continue on? - What,you dare to leave it there?

537
00:53:43,215 --> 00:53:47,805
Safe as a bank,Mr. Greeley, since all know it's mine.

538
00:53:47,965 --> 00:53:53,185
- Is that man drunk? - Dead as Good Friday,miss.

539
00:53:57,475 --> 00:53:59,815
- Good day to you,Mulraney. - Boys.

540
00:54:00,025 --> 00:54:01,735
- Jack. - Slum sociable?

541
00:54:01,905 --> 00:54:04,405
Fact-finding. Reforms-studying.

542
00:54:04,565 --> 00:54:07,035
- May I present...? - The Schermerhorns of Fifth Avenue...

543
00:54:07,195 --> 00:54:09,365
...scarcely require an introduction from you.

544
00:54:09,575 --> 00:54:12,865
Schermerhorn,indeed. Their daughter. This gentleman,of course...

545
00:54:13,035 --> 00:54:16,335
Horace Greeley,the famous publisher. A pleasure and an honor.

546
00:54:16,705 --> 00:54:19,545
- Of the Tribune. - I'm William Cutting.

547
00:54:20,875 --> 00:54:23,255
How do you do,Mr. Cutting?

548
00:54:24,715 --> 00:54:28,885
As of this moment,extremely well, thank you. How do you do?

549
00:54:29,425 --> 00:54:31,475
Orange blossom. Delicious.

550
00:54:31,635 --> 00:54:33,935
- Mr. Cutting is... - What a peach.

551
00:54:34,095 --> 00:54:36,055
She could have a fine career on the stage.

552
00:54:36,225 --> 00:54:38,855
...one of Five Points' local... - A pleasure to meet you.

553
00:54:39,025 --> 00:54:40,525
...leaders. - Mr. Greeley.

554
00:54:40,735 --> 00:54:42,735
- Pleased to meet you. - The Points welcomes you.

555
00:54:42,895 --> 00:54:45,905
You are welcome to these streets and will pass in safety.

556
00:54:47,025 --> 00:54:51,785
Oh,I'll see to their safety. Thank you,Bill. There we are.

557
00:54:51,955 --> 00:54:55,375
Good day,lads. Criminal's braggadocio,you see.

558
00:54:55,535 --> 00:54:59,755
- He knows who I am. - You're well-known in these parts.

559
00:55:00,125 --> 00:55:03,375
I must say that I find that strangely flattering.

560
00:55:03,545 --> 00:55:06,215
- I never did like crushers. - Well,draw it mild,son.

561
00:55:06,425 --> 00:55:10,925
Happy Jack don't fill his lungs without I tell him he may do so.

562
00:55:13,635 --> 00:55:18,565
At the office or store He was kept he'll pretend

563
00:55:18,725 --> 00:55:23,355
And so he was too Drinking rum with a friend

564
00:55:23,525 --> 00:55:27,485
Do you think my watch would be safe up on that lamppost,Bill?

565
00:55:28,825 --> 00:55:31,235
Why don't you hang it up there and see?

566
00:55:34,075 --> 00:55:35,245
Someday.

567
00:55:37,075 --> 00:55:38,585
Someday is right.

568
00:55:40,335 --> 00:55:42,375
This a new lad?

569
00:55:42,875 --> 00:55:48,385
Just another bastard son of Erin I folded in the warmth of my embrace.

570
00:55:51,255 --> 00:55:53,885
- Hey! - I just want to see your face,son.

571
00:55:54,055 --> 00:55:56,225
No harm intended.

572
00:56:05,855 --> 00:56:08,655
Is a kind-loving husband

573
00:56:08,815 --> 00:56:12,615
And a good-tempered wife

574
00:56:19,325 --> 00:56:22,455
You get to know a lot butchering meat.

575
00:56:23,755 --> 00:56:26,295
We're made up of the same things: Flesh and blood...

576
00:56:26,465 --> 00:56:29,755
...tissue,organs.

577
00:56:29,925 --> 00:56:32,635
I love to work with pigs.

578
00:56:32,805 --> 00:56:38,095
The nearest thing in nature to the flesh of a man is the flesh of a pig.

579
00:56:38,265 --> 00:56:40,435
- Pig,huh? - That's right.

580
00:56:40,605 --> 00:56:43,145
This is for you,mother.

581
00:56:45,645 --> 00:56:46,985
There you go.

582
00:56:47,145 --> 00:56:50,155
- God bless you,Mr. Cutting. - God bless you.

583
00:56:50,365 --> 00:56:54,825
- She ain't really my mother. - I knew that,Bill.

584
00:56:58,865 --> 00:57:01,245
This is the liver.

585
00:57:01,705 --> 00:57:03,495
The kidneys.

586
00:57:03,705 --> 00:57:05,545
The heart.

587
00:57:05,705 --> 00:57:09,045
This is a wound. The stomach will bleed and bleed.

588
00:57:09,215 --> 00:57:12,595
This is a kill. This is a kill.

589
00:57:13,425 --> 00:57:16,845
The main artery. This is a kill.

590
00:57:18,225 --> 00:57:20,185
You try.

591
00:57:23,225 --> 00:57:24,685
Go ahead.

592
00:57:50,505 --> 00:57:53,005
The lung. Good. Don't foul the blade on the rib.

593
00:57:53,175 --> 00:57:55,345
Very good. Main artery.

594
00:57:55,505 --> 00:57:58,265
Bleed him slow. Let him think about it for a while.

595
00:57:58,425 --> 00:58:01,305
Slow death. Good.

596
00:58:02,725 --> 00:58:06,065
You'll each bill the city $5000 a month for supplies and services...

597
00:58:06,225 --> 00:58:08,025
...of which you'll receive 10%.

598
00:58:08,185 --> 00:58:12,025
Bill! Mr. Killoran will work out the details. Thank you,gentlemen.

599
00:58:12,195 --> 00:58:15,195
That's how we do things around Tammany,gentlemen.

600
00:58:15,405 --> 00:58:17,325
Who's this then?

601
00:58:18,285 --> 00:58:20,245
Thank you,boys.

602
00:58:20,405 --> 00:58:22,455
Good day,sir.

603
00:58:34,085 --> 00:58:36,595
You got something on your mind?

604
00:58:39,385 --> 00:58:41,435
Bill's taken quite a liking to you.

605
00:58:44,145 --> 00:58:47,935
Now,if you're up to something,bene.

606
00:58:48,145 --> 00:58:50,315
Only I don't want no part in it.

607
00:58:55,025 --> 00:58:58,535
I was in Hellgate for 16 years.

608
00:58:58,905 --> 00:59:01,285
I'm just trying to make my way is all.

609
00:59:01,455 --> 00:59:03,615
Just like you.

610
00:59:04,665 --> 00:59:06,875
Unless,of course, you got a better notion?

611
00:59:08,375 --> 00:59:09,455
No.

612
00:59:10,455 --> 00:59:14,505
Bill,I can't get a day's work done for all the good citizens...

613
00:59:14,675 --> 00:59:18,175
...coming in here to harass me about crime in the Points.

614
00:59:18,345 --> 00:59:20,845
Some even go so far as to accuse Tammany...

615
00:59:21,015 --> 00:59:24,765
...of connivance in this so-called rampant criminality.

616
00:59:24,935 --> 00:59:28,055
What am I to do? I can't have this. Something has to be done.

617
00:59:28,225 --> 00:59:30,605
- What do you have in mind? - I don't know.

618
00:59:30,775 --> 00:59:33,025
I think maybe we should hang someone.

619
00:59:34,315 --> 00:59:36,445
- Who? - No one important,necessarily.

620
00:59:36,615 --> 00:59:41,155
Average men will do. Back-alley amusers with no affiliations.

621
00:59:41,365 --> 00:59:45,035
- How many? - Three or four.

622
00:59:45,365 --> 00:59:48,955
- Which? - Four.

623
00:59:49,535 --> 00:59:53,125
You stand here convicted varyingly...

624
00:59:53,295 --> 00:59:56,375
...of lewdness,jack-rolling...

625
00:59:56,545 --> 01:00:00,345
...sneak-thievery, chloral-hydrating...

626
01:00:00,505 --> 01:00:03,175
...sodomy,strangulation...

627
01:00:03,385 --> 01:00:08,305
...and enthusiastic corruption of the public good.

628
01:00:09,725 --> 01:00:11,685
- We all go someday,huh? - Chin up.

629
01:00:11,855 --> 01:00:14,065
Handsome bunch of gallows fruit. There's my old friend.

630
01:00:14,235 --> 01:00:17,195
- How are you feeling,Arthur? - I'm okay. I'm okay.

631
01:00:17,355 --> 01:00:20,365
Say hello to Amsterdam. Nearly fishhooked McGloin the other day.

632
01:00:20,575 --> 01:00:21,695
- How do you do? - Nearly.

633
01:00:21,865 --> 01:00:23,575
See you dressed for the occasion.

634
01:00:23,745 --> 01:00:25,905
You know me, always like to look me best.

635
01:00:26,075 --> 01:00:27,575
That's the spirit.

636
01:00:29,075 --> 01:00:32,045
Nice locket. I'll give you a dollar for it.

637
01:00:32,205 --> 01:00:33,875
It's me mother's.

638
01:00:34,045 --> 01:00:35,465
Dollar and a half?

639
01:00:36,425 --> 01:00:37,755
Done.

640
01:00:41,255 --> 01:00:42,805
We'll miss you,Arthur.

641
01:00:42,965 --> 01:00:45,135
- See you in the hot country,Seamus. - Hot corn!

642
01:00:45,305 --> 01:00:48,435
Ears of early white corn! Hot corn!

643
01:00:52,605 --> 01:00:54,605
Is my son present here?

644
01:00:56,395 --> 01:00:57,945
Where's my little fella?

645
01:01:00,155 --> 01:01:01,905
Look at your dad.

646
01:01:02,115 --> 01:01:04,155
Farewell,dear boy.

647
01:01:05,575 --> 01:01:10,455
I never struck a foul blow, nor turned a card.

648
01:01:11,955 --> 01:01:15,455
May God greet me as a friend.

649
01:01:39,485 --> 01:01:43,025
And grace my fears relieved

650
01:01:43,195 --> 01:01:47,155
How precious Did that grace appear

651
01:01:47,325 --> 01:01:50,205
That night, the reformers held a dance.

652
01:01:50,365 --> 01:01:52,875
That was the Five Points,all right.

653
01:01:53,035 --> 01:01:56,335
Hangings of a morning, dancings of an evening.

654
01:01:56,505 --> 01:01:58,415
- Sure meself,but...

655
01:01:58,585 --> 01:02:01,425
...it's not a matter of words. I can tell by the way she smiles at me.

656
01:02:01,585 --> 01:02:03,505
- She smiles at a lot of people. - Sir.

657
01:02:03,675 --> 01:02:04,965
You don't know her.

658
01:02:05,175 --> 01:02:08,725
A penny of gratitude for a fighting Irishman,young sir.

659
01:02:11,935 --> 01:02:15,315
- You from Kerry? - I am,sir. I am.

660
01:02:16,265 --> 01:02:18,895
- It ain't much. - Thank you,sir. Thank you.

661
01:02:19,065 --> 01:02:21,655
Ladies and gentlemen, we are delighted to see...

662
01:02:21,815 --> 01:02:25,275
...so many young faces at our first annual Mission dance.

663
01:02:25,445 --> 01:02:27,325
This'll be a real ballum rancum,eh?

664
01:02:27,485 --> 01:02:30,495
The Mission welcomes Christians of every stamp...

665
01:02:30,705 --> 01:02:34,285
...and we are particularly happy to greet our Roman Catholic friends...

666
01:02:34,455 --> 01:02:36,415
...who join us here tonight.

667
01:02:36,665 --> 01:02:40,465
- Ladies! Come with me. Come with me. - Shall we dance?

668
01:02:40,625 --> 01:02:43,505
We're going to start the dancing in just a moment.

669
01:02:43,675 --> 01:02:44,675
No.

670
01:02:45,385 --> 01:02:49,265
- Good evening,Reverend. - Good evening,Your Holiness.

671
01:02:51,345 --> 01:02:52,515
Good evening,Reverend.

672
01:02:52,885 --> 01:02:55,805
Looks as though you should have shaved closer.

673
01:02:59,565 --> 01:03:02,895
Good evening,Reverend. I do beg your pardon.

674
01:03:07,275 --> 01:03:09,115
Miss...?

675
01:03:12,955 --> 01:03:16,205
- Everdeane. - Miss Everdeane.

676
01:03:28,345 --> 01:03:33,305
Now,gentlemen,over here, if you don't mind. Thank you.

677
01:03:33,475 --> 01:03:36,305
Open it. Hold it up.

678
01:03:38,515 --> 01:03:40,475
Into the mirror.

679
01:04:33,155 --> 01:04:34,655
That one.

680
01:04:36,285 --> 01:04:39,665
Our queen has chosen.

681
01:04:58,185 --> 01:04:59,765
Sir...

682
01:04:59,935 --> 01:05:02,395
...your lady. - Right.

683
01:05:02,565 --> 01:05:05,485
Regular services are held at the church at 6 and 8.

684
01:05:05,645 --> 01:05:06,695
Go to hell.

685
01:05:16,155 --> 01:05:18,325
- What do you think you're doing? - Dancing.

686
01:05:18,495 --> 01:05:21,745
- I said,why'd you pick me? - That's none of your business.

687
01:05:21,915 --> 01:05:23,795
Would you mind telling me?

688
01:05:24,375 --> 01:05:25,915
I'm sorry.

689
01:05:26,875 --> 01:05:28,965
Goddamn it!

690
01:05:29,505 --> 01:05:33,255
I'm sorry. I'm not much of a dancer.

691
01:05:33,425 --> 01:05:35,265
Just try to keep calm.

692
01:05:35,425 --> 01:05:39,685
- I never been to a stepping-ken before. - It's best not to look down.

693
01:05:41,805 --> 01:05:44,475
You can hold me tighter if you like.

694
01:05:51,985 --> 01:05:53,905
- All right? - Aye.

695
01:05:55,735 --> 01:05:58,615
So why didn't you dance with Johnny?

696
01:06:00,035 --> 01:06:01,535
Because...

697
01:06:04,165 --> 01:06:06,335
...I didn't want him.

698
01:07:04,595 --> 01:07:06,895
I'm not wanting this.

699
01:07:14,155 --> 01:07:15,115
- Wait. - What?

700
01:07:15,315 --> 01:07:16,865
Wait.

701
01:07:17,735 --> 01:07:18,945
How does this open?

702
01:07:19,115 --> 01:07:23,075
It takes too long to lace back up. We'll be here all night.

703
01:07:34,505 --> 01:07:37,465
Sure,all right,I'll take it off.

704
01:07:58,945 --> 01:08:01,785
There was a baby. They cut it out.

705
01:08:06,165 --> 01:08:07,995
I'm sorry.

706
01:08:09,035 --> 01:08:11,125
Oh,it's fine.

707
01:08:14,875 --> 01:08:17,385
Have you got any scars?

708
01:08:18,885 --> 01:08:20,675
One or two.

709
01:09:18,855 --> 01:09:20,815
What's that,then?

710
01:09:20,985 --> 01:09:22,365
That?

711
01:09:22,575 --> 01:09:24,945
It's a gift from Mr. Cutting.

712
01:09:29,285 --> 01:09:31,075
A gift?

713
01:09:31,745 --> 01:09:33,625
A gift.

714
01:09:34,795 --> 01:09:36,335
Was it your birthday?

715
01:09:37,665 --> 01:09:39,335
No.

716
01:09:43,505 --> 01:09:45,885
What'd you give him,then?

717
01:09:48,015 --> 01:09:50,805
The answer to that has nothing to do with you.

718
01:09:57,605 --> 01:10:00,105
- Don't tell me you're angry with me. - No.

719
01:10:00,695 --> 01:10:02,815
I'm through with you.

720
01:10:06,825 --> 01:10:09,575
Well,you're quicker than most fellows.

721
01:10:09,745 --> 01:10:12,035
Generally,they wait till afterwards.

722
01:10:12,205 --> 01:10:15,205
I ain't interested in the Butcher's leavings.

723
01:10:34,935 --> 01:10:37,435
Hey! Bill says keep clear of the pikers.

724
01:10:37,645 --> 01:10:40,525
- Fifteen to one,Bug-Eye Moran. - Amsterdam!

725
01:10:41,395 --> 01:10:43,695
Everyone was working for the Butcher.

726
01:10:43,865 --> 01:10:45,695
We ran his errands, made his money...

727
01:10:45,865 --> 01:10:47,865
...took a piece and said, "Thank you,sir."

728
01:10:48,035 --> 01:10:50,655
- Gentlemen,it's a raid! - Even Tweed.

729
01:10:50,825 --> 01:10:53,205
- The fight's over. - Even me.

730
01:10:53,375 --> 01:10:56,085
- All right,you stupid... - My father's son.

731
01:10:56,495 --> 01:10:58,665
- What the hell is this? - Sorry,Bill.

732
01:10:58,835 --> 01:11:02,715
The city ordinance against boxiana's a blight,I grant you,but some...

733
01:11:02,875 --> 01:11:05,845
I'm losing revenue while you speechify. Collect those bets!

734
01:11:06,045 --> 01:11:08,055
How do I collect if no one won the fight?

735
01:11:08,215 --> 01:11:11,055
This counts as a "no decision." You got that covered,right?

736
01:11:11,225 --> 01:11:13,185
Didn't anybody pay off the police?

737
01:11:13,345 --> 01:11:16,015
We paid the Municipal Police. This is Metropolitan.

738
01:11:16,185 --> 01:11:18,185
- You'll repay me every cent. - Mr. Tweed...

739
01:11:18,395 --> 01:11:20,565
- Who asked for your opinion? - Let him speak!

740
01:11:20,735 --> 01:11:22,065
He don't answer to you.

741
01:11:22,395 --> 01:11:24,905
The law says there's no boxing in the city,right?

742
01:11:25,065 --> 01:11:28,405
- That's right. In the city. - Well,where does the city end?

743
01:11:35,535 --> 01:11:39,625
The winner,in the 75th round...

744
