- William Tell! - The Butterfly!

994
01:39:52,516 --> 01:39:54,276
- The Tomahawk! - The Spider's Kiss!

995
01:39:54,646 --> 01:39:56,526
The Butcher's Apprentice!

996
01:39:56,686 --> 01:39:58,026
The Butcher's Apprentice.

997
01:39:58,196 --> 01:40:01,486
- Command performance. - Command performance.

998
01:40:01,736 --> 01:40:04,036
- Command performance. - Where have you been?

999
01:40:04,196 --> 01:40:06,656
A command performance indeed!

1000
01:40:06,826 --> 01:40:08,496
- Get out of here. - Don't do it.

1001
01:40:08,666 --> 01:40:13,286
And for this I must beg the indulgence of my former assistant...

1002
01:40:13,456 --> 01:40:15,916
...in matters of impalement.

1003
01:40:16,086 --> 01:40:19,546
The Butcher's original apprentice.

1004
01:40:20,386 --> 01:40:25,466
What do you say,Jen? One more time for the sweet souvenir?

1005
01:40:25,636 --> 01:40:27,556
Come on.

1006
01:40:36,896 --> 01:40:38,986
Don't you do it.

1007
01:40:39,646 --> 01:40:41,906
Good girl,Jenny.

1008
01:40:42,066 --> 01:40:45,906
- Don't be afraid. - What a woman.

1009
01:40:48,496 --> 01:40:50,326
Good evening,Bill.

1010
01:40:50,496 --> 01:40:52,576
She'll be all right.

1011
01:40:55,336 --> 01:40:58,506
- Remember this? - Of course.

1012
01:41:07,266 --> 01:41:12,396
You may feel more comfortable without that garment,Miss Everdeane.

1013
01:41:13,606 --> 01:41:16,766
You'll have to filch me a new one,Bill.

1014
01:41:30,036 --> 01:41:32,536
Anything in your pockets tonight?

1015
01:41:32,706 --> 01:41:35,036
Oh,I ain't started working yet.

1016
01:41:38,206 --> 01:41:41,086
What about that locket that I gave you?

1017
01:41:56,396 --> 01:41:59,816
Apologies,my dear. Pick it up.

1018
01:42:04,656 --> 01:42:06,566
Whoopsie-daisy!

1019
01:42:08,576 --> 01:42:11,076
Now it's good and broke.

1020
01:42:12,076 --> 01:42:14,576
I can't seem to get anything right tonight.

1021
01:42:22,256 --> 01:42:26,086
You got the sand to give them a grand finale?

1022
01:42:34,266 --> 01:42:37,516
Maybe when you're aiming a little straighter.

1023
01:42:45,196 --> 01:42:49,776
Still got some blood in you,Jen? Enough of this heathen music!

1024
01:42:49,946 --> 01:42:53,116
Get rid of these goddamn monkeys. Strike up,boys!

1025
01:42:53,286 --> 01:42:58,706
Ready? This is a night for Americans!

1026
01:43:05,716 --> 01:43:08,216
- Jenny! - Get your hands off me.

1027
01:43:08,386 --> 01:43:11,466
- Go away. - Get your hands off me!

1028
01:43:14,556 --> 01:43:15,806
Move.

1029
01:43:15,976 --> 01:43:18,056
Amsterdam!

1030
01:44:03,226 --> 01:44:05,436
Hats off!

1031
01:44:11,946 --> 01:44:16,656
We hold in our hearts the memory of our fallen brothers...

1032
01:44:16,906 --> 01:44:20,416
...whose blood stains the very streets we walk today.

1033
01:44:21,996 --> 01:44:27,796
Also on this night,we pay tribute to the leader of our enemies...

1034
01:44:29,506 --> 01:44:34,426
...an honorable man who crossed over bravely...

1035
01:44:34,596 --> 01:44:37,266
...fighting for what he believed in.

1036
01:44:43,436 --> 01:44:48,106
To defeat my enemy, I extinguish his life...

1037
01:44:48,276 --> 01:44:52,276
...and consume him as I consume these flames.

1038
01:44:53,696 --> 01:44:55,946
In honor of Priest Vallon.

1039
01:45:04,456 --> 01:45:05,996
That's a wound.

1040
01:45:06,376 --> 01:45:08,716
God!

1041
01:45:15,256 --> 01:45:20,386
I want you all to meet the son of Priest Vallon.

1042
01:45:20,556 --> 01:45:23,226
I took him under my wing...

1043
01:45:23,396 --> 01:45:25,186
...and see how I'm repaid?

1044
01:45:25,356 --> 01:45:27,526
- You bastard! - Saves my life one day...

1045
01:45:27,686 --> 01:45:30,236
...so he can kill me the next like a sneak-thief...

1046
01:45:30,396 --> 01:45:33,406
...instead of fighting like a man.

1047
01:45:33,866 --> 01:45:38,116
A base defiler, unworthy of a noble name.

1048
01:45:40,536 --> 01:45:42,956
God! Jesus!

1049
01:45:51,376 --> 01:45:54,426
All right,that'll do,McGloin. Splay him out.

1050
01:45:55,596 --> 01:46:00,386
This show ain't for blackies. You! You get to watch.

1051
01:46:01,886 --> 01:46:04,556
Don't you hear,nigger?

1052
01:46:05,936 --> 01:46:09,726
This is fresh meat. You know what I mean?

1053
01:46:09,896 --> 01:46:13,196
We need to tenderize this meat a little bit.

1054
01:46:13,356 --> 01:46:17,196
All right,let's kiss good night to that pretty young face of yours.

1055
01:46:21,826 --> 01:46:23,076
No!

1056
01:46:27,586 --> 01:46:29,586
No!

1057
01:46:30,666 --> 01:46:34,586
What'll it be,then? Rib or chop? Loin or shank?

1058
01:46:34,756 --> 01:46:36,716
- The liver! - The spleen!

1059
01:46:36,926 --> 01:46:38,596
- The tongue! - Kidneys!

1060
01:46:44,936 --> 01:46:47,056
- The lungs! - The liver!

1061
01:46:47,226 --> 01:46:49,066
- The tongue! - The kidneys!

1062
01:46:49,266 --> 01:46:51,566
- The stomach! - The heart! The heart!

1063
01:46:51,726 --> 01:46:54,236
The heart? This boy has no heart.

1064
01:46:54,446 --> 01:46:57,196
- Then kill him! - Kill him!

1065
01:47:02,446 --> 01:47:07,076
He ain't earned a death. He ain't earned a death at my hands.

1066
01:47:07,376 --> 01:47:11,876
No. He'll walk amongst you marked with shame...

1067
01:47:12,046 --> 01:47:17,466
...a freak worthy of Barnum's Museum of Wonders.

1068
01:47:17,636 --> 01:47:21,056
God's only man spared by the Butcher.

1069
01:47:21,216 --> 01:47:22,636
No,Bill!

1070
01:47:23,806 --> 01:47:26,806
No! No!

1071
01:47:27,186 --> 01:47:30,646
No! No! No!

1072
01:47:30,816 --> 01:47:34,276
No! No! No!

1073
01:48:00,676 --> 01:48:02,846
Here. Here!

1074
01:48:03,056 --> 01:48:05,476
This way. Come on. Come on!

1075
01:48:51,516 --> 01:48:53,816
I wanna show you something.

1076
01:48:58,696 --> 01:49:01,866
My mother's bones share this grave.

1077
01:49:03,866 --> 01:49:08,536
I've saved 10 cents out of every dollar I've ever earned since I was 13.

1078
01:49:08,706 --> 01:49:10,826
That's $215.

1079
01:49:10,996 --> 01:49:16,796
That's $215 for bludgeting and the rest.

1080
01:49:20,216 --> 01:49:24,046
This is what I wanted to show you.

1081
01:49:24,216 --> 01:49:26,926
This is where we're gonna go as soon as you get well.

1082
01:49:27,636 --> 01:49:32,096
San Francisco,California.

1083
01:49:34,806 --> 01:49:37,476
You can have anything you want out there.

1084
01:49:37,646 --> 01:49:43,526
These men are pulling gold right out of the river with their own hands.

1085
01:49:45,326 --> 01:49:49,656
We're here,and we need to get there.

1086
01:49:50,406 --> 01:49:55,916
We start here,go down around here...

1087
01:49:57,996 --> 01:50:00,626
...to San Francisco.

1088
01:50:02,176 --> 01:50:04,216
Shortest way to go.

1089
01:50:05,006 --> 01:50:07,506
Would you go with me?

1090
01:50:32,156 --> 01:50:35,876
No need to fire that,miss. Or even aim it.

1091
01:50:36,376 --> 01:50:39,836
An audience with your mangled friend is all I want.

1092
01:50:55,226 --> 01:50:57,356
I got 44 notches in my club.

1093
01:50:59,646 --> 01:51:01,566
Do you know what they're for?

1094
01:51:03,736 --> 01:51:06,696
To remind me of what I owe God when I die.

1095
01:51:13,706 --> 01:51:16,536
My father was killed in battle too.

1096
01:51:17,206 --> 01:51:20,166
In Ireland,in the streets...

1097
01:51:21,876 --> 01:51:24,586
...fighting those who would take as their privilege...

1098
01:51:24,756 --> 01:51:29,046
...what could only be got and held by the decimation of a race.

1099
01:51:29,716 --> 01:51:33,016
That war is 1000 years old or more.

1100
01:51:33,726 --> 01:51:36,596
We never expected it to follow us here.

1101
01:51:38,556 --> 01:51:40,606
It didn't.

1102
01:51:40,766 --> 01:51:43,436
It was waiting for us when we landed.

1103
01:51:47,106 --> 01:51:51,576
Your father tried to carve out a corner in this country for his tribe.

1104
01:51:53,326 --> 01:51:56,246
That was him. That was his Dead Rabbits.

1105
01:51:59,126 --> 01:52:02,746
I often wondered, if he'd lived a bit longer...

1106
01:52:03,586 --> 01:52:06,216
...would he have wanted a bit more?

1107
01:52:17,596 --> 01:52:20,856
Why'd you rifle through his pockets then?

1108
01:52:37,956 --> 01:52:40,376
For safekeeping.

1109
01:52:43,286 --> 01:52:45,706
I thought maybe you could do with it.

1110
01:53:07,316 --> 01:53:10,406
The blood stays on the blade.

1111
01:54:27,016 --> 01:54:29,186
That's a sorry-looking pelt.

1112
01:54:33,736 --> 01:54:37,736
And it's been so nice and quiet for the last three months.

1113
01:54:39,946 --> 01:54:43,536
Tell me,this charge, does it sit uneasy with you?

1114
01:54:44,706 --> 01:54:46,876
No,it's...

1115
01:54:47,786 --> 01:54:50,256
...not uneasy,Bill.

1116
01:54:51,046 --> 01:54:53,586
No,I wouldn't say that.

1117
01:54:55,546 --> 01:55:00,716
But my allegiance is to the law.

1118
01:55:01,766 --> 01:55:04,436
I'm paid to uphold the law.

1119
01:55:20,326 --> 01:55:23,826
What in heaven's name are you talking about?

1120
01:55:27,916 --> 01:55:30,666
You may have misgivings, but don't go believing that.

1121
01:55:30,836 --> 01:55:33,506
That way lies damnation.

1122
01:55:36,676 --> 01:55:39,756
I'm in no danger of damnation,Bill.

1123
01:55:50,976 --> 01:55:53,186
Here's the thing.

1124
01:55:54,276 --> 01:55:57,236
I don't give a tuppenny fuck about your moral conundrum...

1125
01:55:57,406 --> 01:56:00,366
...you meatheaded shit-sack.

1126
01:56:01,696 --> 01:56:04,446
That's more or less the thing.

1127
01:56:05,786 --> 01:56:08,956
And I want you to go out there... You,nobody else.

1128
01:56:09,126 --> 01:56:13,546
None of your little minions. I want you to go out there...

1129
01:56:13,706 --> 01:56:15,876
...and I want you...

1130
01:56:16,836 --> 01:56:20,716
...to punish the person...

1131
01:56:20,886 --> 01:56:23,386
...who's responsible...

1132
01:56:25,516 --> 01:56:30,226
...for murdering this poor little rabbit.

1133
01:56:36,236 --> 01:56:38,396
Is that understood?

1134
01:56:42,236 --> 01:56:44,036
Right.

1135
01:56:45,246 --> 01:56:48,866
Help yourself to some decent meat on the way out.

1136
01:57:25,986 --> 01:57:27,826
Damn it.

1137
01:57:29,496 --> 01:57:31,536
Is that you,boy?

1138
01:57:32,576 --> 01:57:35,086
I didn't mean nothing by that shot,you know.

1139
01:57:36,586 --> 01:57:39,336
You scared me is all.

1140
01:57:41,506 --> 01:57:44,426
Sure you know I'd never do you harm.

1141
01:57:45,256 --> 01:57:47,676
Come out now,lad.

1142
01:57:49,926 --> 01:57:52,686
Remember your father and me.

1143
01:57:55,766 --> 01:57:59,526
Are you too young to remember your old Uncle Jack?

1144
01:58:01,356 --> 01:58:04,026
Oh,the times we had.

1145
01:58:09,616 --> 01:58:12,036
You know I won't hurt you.

1146
01:58:33,686 --> 01:58:35,726
Is he dead?

1147
01:58:35,896 --> 01:58:39,316
I'm gonna get Andrew. Andrew,come see.

1148
01:58:39,526 --> 01:58:43,736
Andrew,come see,quick! Everybody,quick!

1149
01:58:43,906 --> 01:58:48,576
This is bad for everybody. What's next? Dead politicians?

1150
01:58:49,536 --> 01:58:54,666
I could spare half a dozen of you easier than I can spare him.

1151
01:58:55,416 --> 01:58:59,166
Still,I think it shows dash.

1152
01:58:59,336 --> 01:59:03,336
Give the boy some time. We'll settle with a good dustup.

1153
01:59:46,716 --> 01:59:50,216
There's more of us coming off these ships every day.

1154
01:59:50,886 --> 01:59:54,556
I heard 15,000 Irish a week.

1155
01:59:55,556 --> 01:59:58,016
And we're afraid of the Natives.

1156
02:00:00,016 --> 02:00:04,526
Get all of us together, we ain't got a gang. We got an army.

1157
02:00:04,686 --> 02:00:07,356
And all you need's a spark,right? Just one spark.

1158
02:00:07,526 --> 02:00:10,066
Something to wake us all up.

1159
02:00:26,626 --> 02:00:29,296
It was me played you false.

1160
02:00:31,136 --> 02:00:34,716
- I'd take it back if I could. - Take it back?

1161
02:00:38,306 --> 02:00:40,896
Johnny,I gotta kill you.

1162
02:00:54,656 --> 02:00:57,906
Get out of the Points and don't come back.

1163
02:01:05,416 --> 02:01:07,836
Where you going,boyo?

1164
02:01:08,836 --> 02:01:10,336
Come along.

1165
02:01:10,506 --> 02:01:12,346
Come on.

1166
02:01:14,756 --> 02:01:17,676
Tell us,John,what's the trouble?

1167
02:01:18,516 --> 02:01:20,306
No trouble,Bill.

1168
02:01:23,356 --> 02:01:25,976
Still hiding out with your friends?

1169
02:01:29,106 --> 02:01:33,776
No,I'm... I'm not with them,Bill.

1170
02:01:33,946 --> 02:01:37,076
I'm with you. I'm with the Natives.

1171
02:01:41,616 --> 02:01:45,876
You always was a Native as far as I'm interested,John...

1172
02:01:48,206 --> 02:01:51,126
...till you became a stag.

1173
02:01:54,546 --> 02:01:58,216
You tell me you're a Native. Do you want to know what a Native is?

1174
02:02:00,056 --> 02:02:03,556
A Native is a man...

1175
02:02:03,726 --> 02:02:08,436
...what's willing to give his life for his country...

1176
02:02:10,316 --> 02:02:12,656
...like my father done.

1177
02:02:15,736 --> 02:02:19,746
Are you willing to do that, my young friend?

1178
02:02:28,706 --> 02:02:31,926
John. Johnny!

1179
02:02:39,426 --> 02:02:41,426
Johnny?

1180
02:02:50,856 --> 02:02:52,856
John...

1181
02:03:05,116 --> 02:03:07,956
It hurts too much.

1182
02:03:14,006 --> 02:03:16,176
Just kill me.

1183
02:03:20,766 --> 02:03:23,176
Just kill me.

1184
02:03:24,766 --> 02:03:28,016
Please,please.

1185
02:03:35,526 --> 02:03:37,616
Please.

1186
02:03:39,826 --> 02:03:41,786
Please.

1187
02:03:45,866 --> 02:03:48,376
I'm sorry,Johnny.

1188
02:04:03,806 --> 02:04:07,766
Holy Mary,mother of God,pray for us sinners now and at the hour of our death.

1189
02:04:07,976 --> 02:04:09,896
Amen.

1190
02:04:10,646 --> 02:04:12,976
Rest in peace,Ma.

1191
02:04:15,696 --> 02:04:18,066
What're you doing here,boyo?

1192
02:04:24,326 --> 02:04:27,666
What's a nigger doing in this church?

1193
02:04:31,916 --> 02:04:34,166
What's a Dead Rabbit doing with the Natives?

1194
02:04:34,336 --> 02:04:37,506
There's no niggers in the Natives. Natives and Rabbits is one thing.

1195
02:04:37,676 --> 02:04:39,676
A nigger in the church is something else!

1196
02:04:39,886 --> 02:04:41,756
You run with the Natives, pray with them!

1197
02:04:41,926 --> 02:04:45,056
You're gonna wind up on a stake like your man did!

1198
02:04:45,806 --> 02:04:47,096
McGloin.

1199
02:04:47,266 --> 02:04:51,686
Father! Jesus,did you know there's a nigger in your church?

1200
02:05:09,706 --> 02:05:12,206
Jesus.

1201
02:05:34,686 --> 02:05:37,236
The earth turns...

1202
02:05:38,026 --> 02:05:40,736
...but we don't feel it move.

1203
02:05:43,366 --> 02:05:46,196
Then one night you look up.

1204
02:05:47,196 --> 02:05:52,416
One spark,and the sky is on fire.

1205
02:06:03,636 --> 02:06:06,556
It's a touching spectacle.

1206
02:06:08,266 --> 02:06:11,386
We'll come back when you're ready for us.

1207
02:06:17,646 --> 02:06:21,486
The past is the torch that lights our way.

1208
02:06:21,736 --> 02:06:27,156
Where our fathers have shown us the path,we shall follow.

1209
02:06:28,996 --> 02:06:33,326
Our faith is the weapon most feared by our enemies.

1210
02:06:33,626 --> 02:06:38,496
For thereby shall we lift our people up against those who would destroy us.

1211
02:06:38,666 --> 02:06:43,586
Our name is called the Dead Rabbits to remind all of our suffering...

1212
02:06:43,756 --> 02:06:47,636
...and as a call to those who suffer still tojoin our ranks...

1213
02:06:47,806 --> 02:06:52,596
...however so far they may have strayed from our common home across the sea.

1214
02:06:52,766 --> 02:06:56,436
For with great numbers must come great strength...

1215
02:06:58,186 --> 02:07:00,356
...and the salvation of our people.

1216
02:07:00,856 --> 02:07:03,236
- We don't want your business. - How many men live here?

1217
02:07:03,396 --> 02:07:05,946
- You have to register. - You can't force me to join.

1218
02:07:06,116 --> 02:07:07,826
- Have you got $300? - Of course not.

1219
02:07:07,986 --> 02:07:11,406
- Who's got $300? - Lf you are drafted,release from service...

1220
02:07:11,576 --> 02:07:14,996
...can only be secured for $300, according to the Conscription Act.

1221
02:07:15,166 --> 02:07:17,786
- Otherwise,you have to serve! - Who the hell's got $300?

1222
02:07:17,956 --> 02:07:21,626
You have to serve,sir, unless you have $300!

1223
02:07:21,796 --> 02:07:23,756
- Boys! - Go back to where you came from!

1224
02:07:23,926 --> 02:07:28,296
I'm born in this country. You immigrated here. You will fight for this country!

1225
02:07:28,466 --> 02:07:31,176
Sweet Jesus! War does terrible things to men.

1226
02:07:31,346 --> 02:07:37,356
- Get back uptown where you belong! - $300? So it's another rich man's war.

1227
02:07:37,516 --> 02:07:40,606
Sir,I request an audience with this man.

1228
02:07:42,646 --> 02:07:44,856
No one speak English in New York anymore?

1229
02:07:45,026 --> 02:07:47,116
- Don't understand. - You do speak English.

1230
02:07:49,076 --> 02:07:53,446
I wonder if Miss Everdeane could angle her rifle in some other direction.

1231
02:07:58,786 --> 02:08:03,546
I wonder,Mr. Vallon,if you understand the true value of this sort of publicity.

1232
02:08:07,466 --> 02:08:11,426
The archbishop himself,shoulder to shoulder with the Irish in the Five Points.

1233
02:08:11,966 --> 02:08:15,136
I'm offering to form an alliance with you against Bill Cutting...

1234
02:08:15,306 --> 02:08:18,056
...and his slate of Nativist candidates.

1235
02:08:18,226 --> 02:08:22,186
I'll negotiate a handsome fee for every Irish vote you send Tammany's way...

1236
02:08:22,396 --> 02:08:24,736
...in the coming elections.

1237
02:08:26,146 --> 02:08:29,316
I need a new friend in the Five Points,son.

1238
02:08:32,406 --> 02:08:34,826
I'd like that friend to be you.

1239
02:08:38,076 --> 02:08:40,746
Now,just a moment, Mr. Tweed.

1240
02:08:40,916 --> 02:08:44,126
Suppose we do get you those votes.

1241
02:08:46,466 --> 02:08:48,716
Would you back an Irish candidate of my choosing?

1242
02:08:48,926 --> 02:08:51,886
- I don't think so. - What if we get you all the Irish votes?

1243
02:08:52,176 --> 02:08:55,926
That will only happen in the reign of Queen Dick.

1244
02:08:57,886 --> 02:09:00,096
- Beg your pardon? - It will never happen.

1245
02:09:00,266 --> 02:09:03,726
I might be persuaded to back an Irish candidate for,say,alderman.

1246
02:09:03,896 --> 02:09:06,686
- Alderman? - We've already got Irish aldermen.

1247
02:09:06,856 --> 02:09:10,276
- So we have. That's why... - Well,what's bigger than alderman?

1248
02:09:11,696 --> 02:09:15,496
Sheriff. Sheriff. All right,Mr. Tweed.

1249
02:09:15,656 --> 02:09:19,616
You back an Irishman for sheriff of the city and county of New York...

1250
02:09:19,786 --> 02:09:21,166
...and we'll get him elected.

1251
02:09:21,326 --> 02:09:24,706
I love the Irish,but higher than alderman you shall never climb.

1252
02:09:24,876 --> 02:09:27,376
- Well,why not? - For one thing,no man living...

1253
02:09:27,546 --> 02:09:29,336
...can consolidate the Irish vote. - I can.

1254
02:09:29,506 --> 02:09:31,716
And for another, I mean no effrontery...

1255
02:09:31,886 --> 02:09:36,136
...no one's yet found an Irish candidate for sheriff worth voting for.

1256
02:09:38,516 --> 02:09:39,886
Monk.

1257
02:09:40,976 --> 02:09:42,266
Here.

1258
02:09:46,776 --> 02:09:49,446
He's to have me looking as sober as me own grandfather.

1259
02:09:49,606 --> 02:09:53,776
- Another great man,I'm sure. - A thorough drunken bastard.

1260
02:09:55,826 --> 02:09:57,576
Could I say what I want?

1261
02:09:58,746 --> 02:10:01,076
Well,that's why I wanted you.

1262
02:10:01,246 --> 02:10:04,166
Our elected representatives are a gang of thieves...

1263
02:10:04,336 --> 02:10:06,086
...who swear to better our lot...

1264
02:10:06,246 --> 02:10:09,166
...while dipping their hands deep into our pockets.

1265
02:10:09,336 --> 02:10:13,006
I stand shoulder to shoulder with community leaders like Bill Cutting...

1266
02:10:13,426 --> 02:10:17,346
...against any and all inroads into our fine democracy.

1267
02:10:17,516 --> 02:10:21,686
I'll see to it that no one takes away what you've earned by pluck and application.

1268
02:10:21,896 --> 02:10:23,936
- To invading hordes of Hibernians!

1269
02:10:24,106 --> 02:10:28,146
You go to the polls and you put your mark next to the name Walter McGinn.

1270
02:10:28,316 --> 02:10:32,986
- Against the potato eaters,like them over there,thieving our jobs!

1271
02:10:33,156 --> 02:10:35,526
Why should so many Irish die down south...

1272
02:10:35,696 --> 02:10:40,326
...when the first war to win is not down in Dixie,but right here in these streets?

1273
02:10:42,206 --> 02:10:44,956
And who's the finest street fighter in the Five Points?

1274
02:10:45,166 --> 02:10:47,336
- Monk! - That's right.

1275
02:10:47,496 --> 02:10:50,256
Now,let the whole damn city hear it!

1276
02:10:51,716 --> 02:10:53,506
That man was right born for this.

1277
02:10:53,676 --> 02:10:56,716
Well,he's killed 44 men, laid low a couple hundred more.

1278
02:10:56,886 --> 02:10:58,556
- Is that right? - That's right.

1279
02:10:58,766 --> 02:11:00,806
I should have run him for mayor.

1280
02:11:03,016 --> 02:11:06,306
All right,line them up. It's election day!

1281
02:11:06,806 --> 02:11:10,146
Not so fast, you little yellow bastard!

1282
02:11:10,396 --> 02:11:12,196
Come on!

1283
02:11:15,906 --> 02:11:17,906
Come on,you bastard, we need your vote.

1284
02:11:18,076 --> 02:11:21,496
Bastard? I fought for you,nigger. I lost an arm for you.

1285
02:11:21,656 --> 02:11:23,496
Well,that's a start. Now,come on.

1286
02:11:23,666 --> 02:11:25,416
Rise and shine. Rise and shine.

1287
02:11:25,626 --> 02:11:28,746
In this great country of ours, even the hop fiends get to vote!

1288
02:11:30,046 --> 02:11:31,916
Less art and more haste,Don.

1289
02:11:32,086 --> 02:11:34,546
- Where are you going? - I already voted today.

1290
02:11:34,716 --> 02:11:37,716
Cast for Monk and Tammany, by God. Twice.

1291
02:11:37,926 --> 02:11:41,716
Twice? Only twice? You call that doing your civic duty? Come with me.

1292
02:11:41,886 --> 02:11:44,516
Oh,no,you don't. Get back and sit down.

1293
02:11:44,686 --> 02:11:46,766
Here's another one. Clean him up good.

1294
02:11:46,936 --> 02:11:49,606
Shave their beards and send them back to vote again.

1295
02:11:49,816 --> 02:11:52,646
All right,boys. Vote Monk,Tammany. Monk,Tammany!

1296
02:11:52,816 --> 02:11:55,906
So,gentlemen,what our great city needs is a new courthouse.

1297
02:11:56,106 --> 02:11:58,946
I propose it should be a modest, economical structure.

1298
02:11:59,116 --> 02:12:00,906
Excuse me one moment.

1299
02:12:01,076 --> 02:12:04,616
Monk's already won by 3000 more votes than there are voters.

1300
02:12:04,786 --> 02:12:08,326
Three? Make it 20,30. We don't need a victory. We need a Roman triumph!

1301
02:12:08,496 --> 02:12:12,756
- But we don't have any more ballots. - Remember the first rule of politics:

1302
02:12:12,956 --> 02:12:16,296
The ballots don't make the results, the counters make the results.

1303
02:12:16,466 --> 02:12:17,586
Keep counting.

1304
02:12:49,496 --> 02:12:51,456
It's from Bill.

1305
02:12:54,876 --> 02:12:56,466
Monk.

1306
02:13:16,236 --> 02:13:19,196
Citizens of the Five Points...

1307
02:13:19,696 --> 02:13:23,616
...Mr. Bill Cutting is attempting to draw me into an argument...

1308
02:13:23,786 --> 02:13:28,366
...that would no doubt end in bloodshed and the compromising of my office.

1309
02:13:29,036 --> 02:13:30,996
What do you think?

1310
02:13:31,916 --> 02:13:35,586
Should I engage in silence this relic of the ancient law?

1311
02:13:35,756 --> 02:13:42,176
Or shall I be your chosen voice in a new testament,in the new world?

1312
02:13:48,136 --> 02:13:49,936
There you are,Bill.

1313
02:13:51,596 --> 02:13:53,566
The people have spoken.

1314
02:13:55,066 --> 02:13:59,146
The very notion of violent reprisal benumbs them.

1315
02:14:01,406 --> 02:14:03,066
Come on up.

1316
02:14:03,616 --> 02:14:07,076
Let's see if we can resolve our grievances the democratic way.

1317
02:14:30,306 --> 02:14:35,106
That,my friends, is the minority vote.

1318
02:14:36,146 --> 02:14:40,196
Now you've tasted my mutton. How do you like it?

1319
02:14:40,356 --> 02:14:41,776
Look.

1320
02:14:41,946 --> 02:14:44,446
I want you to see this.

1321
02:14:47,326 --> 02:14:49,406
This is you. Right here.

1322
02:14:49,576 --> 02:14:53,456
Notch 45,you Irish bog bastard.

1323
02:15:04,926 --> 02:15:08,426
Why don't you burn him, see if his ashes turn green.

1324
02:15:13,726 --> 02:15:16,106
Fortune favors the bold!

1325
02:15:28,536 --> 02:15:32,616
- You killed an elected official? - Who elected him?

1326
02:15:32,786 --> 02:15:35,956
You don't know what you've done to yourself.

1327
02:15:41,506 --> 02:15:44,006
I know your works.

1328
02:15:44,676 --> 02:15:46,836
You are neither cold nor hot.

1329
02:15:47,006 --> 02:15:51,306
So because you are lukewarm, I will spew you out of my mouth.

1330
02:15:52,886 --> 02:15:55,396
You can build your filthy world without me.

1331
02:15:55,556 --> 02:15:58,016
I took the father. Now I'll take the son.

1332
02:15:58,186 --> 02:16:03,106
You tell young Vallon I'm gonna paint Paradise Square with his blood.

1333
02:16:03,356 --> 02:16:04,946
Two coats.

1334
02:16:05,526 --> 02:16:08,196
I'll festoon my bedchamber with his guts.

1335
02:16:08,366 --> 02:16:10,866
As for you, Mr. Tammany-fucking-Hall...

1336
02:16:11,036 --> 02:16:12,906
...you come down to the Points again...

1337
02:16:13,076 --> 02:16:16,576
...and you'll be dispatched by mine own hand.

1338
02:16:18,376 --> 02:16:23,756
Now get back to your celebration and let me eat in peace. I paid you fair.

1339
02:16:47,566 --> 02:16:49,276
Stop.

1340
02:16:50,276 --> 02:16:51,866
Raise.

1341
02:17:34,986 --> 02:17:37,206
You son of a bitch!

1342
02:17:41,036 --> 02:17:43,036
Challenge.

1343
02:17:44,416 --> 02:17:46,796
Challenge accepted.

1344
02:18:38,516 --> 02:18:41,896
And then it came, the first day of the draft.

1345
02:18:42,056 --> 02:18:47,436
Thomas O'Neill. Andrew Lewis. Joseph Flynn.

1346
02:18:47,606 --> 02:18:50,856
They read out the draftees' names like they was dead already.

1347
02:18:51,026 --> 02:18:55,366
Andrew Martin. J.B. Gleason.

1348
02:18:55,526 --> 02:18:58,236
- The O'Connell Guard. - The Plug Uglies.

1349
02:18:58,406 --> 02:19:01,656
- As for us,the tribes were gathered. - Forty Thieves.

1350
02:19:01,996 --> 02:19:04,496
- The Chichesters. - The drums was beating.

1351
02:19:04,706 --> 02:19:05,996
The Dead Rabbits.

1352
02:19:06,166 --> 02:19:09,126
- The American Guard. - The Atlantic Guard.

1353
02:19:09,296 --> 02:19:11,966
- The Slaughter Housers. - The Bowery Boys.

1354
02:19:12,126 --> 02:19:14,466
The Confederation of American Natives.

1355
02:19:15,886 --> 02:19:17,056
James Mooney.

1356
02:19:17,216 --> 02:19:20,676
But all we could see was the hand in front of us.

1357
02:19:20,886 --> 02:19:22,846
Sean O'Connell.

1358
02:19:23,056 --> 02:19:27,186
G.W. Morris. John Doyle.

1359
02:19:27,396 --> 02:19:30,026
- When? - Whenever you like.

1360
02:19:30,236 --> 02:19:32,396
- Daybreak tomorrow. - Ground?

1361
02:19:32,566 --> 02:19:34,696
Paradise Square.

1362
02:19:34,906 --> 02:19:36,656
Weapons?

1363
02:19:36,816 --> 02:19:42,076
- That I leave up to you. - Bricks,bats,axes,knives...

1364
02:19:42,456 --> 02:19:43,866
Pistols?

1365
02:19:45,416 --> 02:19:46,876
No pistols.

1366
02:19:47,996 --> 02:19:50,046
Good boy.

1367
02:19:52,586 --> 02:19:55,636
The terms are resolved. The council's concluded.

1368
02:19:57,546 --> 02:20:01,596
Thomas McEvoy. W.H. Miles.

1369
02:20:01,766 --> 02:20:04,846
- To hell with your damned draft! - Give them hellfire,boys!

1370
02:20:05,016 --> 02:20:06,556
Rip them apart!

1371
02:20:13,606 --> 02:20:16,156
Kill the rich bastards!

1372
02:20:22,366 --> 02:20:23,996
Uptown!

1373
02:20:25,576 --> 02:20:27,376
You're not getting my son!

1374
02:20:32,956 --> 02:20:35,626
Uptown at the draft office...

1375
02:20:35,796 --> 02:20:40,806
...the cops broke a few skulls, and everybody run away.

1376
02:20:41,806 --> 02:20:44,226
But the word was spreading...

1377
02:20:44,386 --> 02:20:46,266
...and the dark.

1378
02:20:47,476 --> 02:20:48,806
Up on Fifth Avenue...

1379
02:20:48,976 --> 02:20:52,316
...the Schermerhorns and their mob breathed a little easy.

1380
02:20:52,526 --> 02:20:55,486
Just a brief burst of anger over Mr. Lincoln's draft.

1381
02:20:55,696 --> 02:20:57,906
Entirely justifiable in my view.

1382
02:20:58,066 --> 02:21:01,826
- There are two sides to that question... - There are several sides...

1383
02:21:01,986 --> 02:21:04,496
...but only one right side, as with any question...

1384
02:21:04,696 --> 02:21:06,956
...that involves the abuse of executive power.

1385
02:21:07,166 --> 02:21:09,456
In any case,Mr. Greeley...

1386
02:21:09,626 --> 02:21:12,336
...we can all be thankful that it wasn't any worse.

1387
02:21:12,546 --> 02:21:15,626
It may be worse yet. I saw them. I don't know what to think.

1388
02:21:15,836 --> 02:21:19,006
Now what is it that you are so fond of saying,Mr. Tweed?

1389
02:21:19,176 --> 02:21:21,636
Mr. Greeley,you won't like this. But what is it?

1390
02:21:21,796 --> 02:21:22,846
I don't remember.

1391
02:21:23,056 --> 02:21:27,766
"You can always hire one half of the poor to kill the other half."

1392
02:21:38,026 --> 02:21:40,366
I've come to say goodbye.

1393
02:21:40,526 --> 02:21:43,486
I've booked passage for California.

1394
02:21:45,996 --> 02:21:48,786
Jenny,give me one more day, and I'll go with you.

1395
02:21:48,956 --> 02:21:51,286
You'll be dead by then.

1396
02:21:51,826 --> 02:21:55,296
- Well,what would you have me do? - I don't know.

1397
02:21:57,916 --> 02:22:01,676
- This will all be finished tomorrow. - No,it won't.

1398
02:22:03,296 --> 02:22:04,846
No.

1399
02:22:05,266 --> 02:22:08,386
This whole place is gonna burn anyway.

1400
02:22:16,436 --> 02:22:21,196
I've heard that the poor are going from door to door in the Five Points...

1401
02:22:21,356 --> 02:22:24,906
...asking those supporters who wish to see further riots...

1402
02:22:25,076 --> 02:22:28,246
...to place a lighted candle in the window.

1403
02:22:28,616 --> 02:22:30,706
Irish,Poles,Germans,all of them.

1404
02:22:31,496 --> 02:22:37,706
Mr. Greeley,the city is not mad. I prophesy a very dark night.

1405
02:22:59,776 --> 02:23:03,776
Nobody goes to work today! We'll shut the factories down!

1406
02:23:03,946 --> 02:23:08,366
When the sun rose next, the city had split in half.

1407
02:23:08,536 --> 02:23:10,366
From all over New York they came:

1408
02:23:10,536 --> 02:23:13,366
Ironworkers,factory boys, street cleaners...

1409
02:23:13,536 --> 02:23:15,126
...Irish,Polish,German...

1410
02:23:15,336 --> 02:23:18,086
...anyone who never cared about slavery or the Union...

1411
02:23:18,296 --> 02:23:20,836
...anyone who couldn't buy his way out.

1412
02:23:21,006 --> 02:23:24,006
"Let the sons of the rich go and die," they cried.

1413
02:23:24,176 --> 02:23:27,216
"Let the sons of the poor stay home."

1414
02:23:28,636 --> 02:23:30,766
The earth was shaking now.

1415
02:23:30,926 --> 02:23:33,646
But I was about my father's business.

1416
02:23:38,726 --> 02:23:40,986
A bunch of Fifth Avenue scums!

1417
02:23:48,156 --> 02:23:52,616
Almighty Lord, you are the dagger in my hand.

1418
02:23:53,916 --> 02:23:56,326
Guide my hand on this day of vengeance.

1419
02:23:56,496 --> 02:24:00,456
We give thanks to the Lord, for he is good.

1420
02:24:00,626 --> 02:24:04,966
With you,the swift cannot flee, nor the strong escape.

1421
02:24:05,126 --> 02:24:09,306
Let my sword devour until its thirst is quenched with blood...

1422
02:24:09,506 --> 02:24:11,466
...and my enemies sleep forever.

1423
02:24:11,676 --> 02:24:14,016
For you are the Lord God of Retribution.

1424
02:24:14,186 --> 02:24:16,646
For the Lord crushes the wicked.

1425
02:24:16,806 --> 02:24:19,436
The Lord is merciful...

1426
02:24:20,066 --> 02:24:23,856
...and his love endures forever.

1427
02:24:24,396 --> 02:24:25,776
- Amen. - Amen.

1428
02:24:25,946 --> 02:24:26,446
Amen.

1429
02:24:26,446 --> 02:24:27,116
Amen.

1430
02:24:33,116 --> 02:24:36,166
- Run away,you sons of bitches! - Come on out!

1431
02:24:38,706 --> 02:24:42,836
- Upstairs! Get the women upstairs! - Father! Father!

1432
02:24:46,676 --> 02:24:49,136
Let's take the bastards!

1433
02:24:50,216 --> 02:24:54,176
From 18th Precinct: The mob are sacking houses,27th Street and Seventh Avenue.

1434
02:24:54,386 --> 02:24:55,726
We have no force to send.

1435
02:24:55,936 --> 02:24:59,186
16th Precinct: All the stores are closing on Eighth Avenue...

1436
02:24:59,356 --> 02:25:01,316
...from fear of the mob in 17th Street.

1437
02:25:01,516 --> 02:25:04,026
Show us what you got, you cowardly bastards!

1438
02:25:05,816 --> 02:25:08,906
From 4th: The rioters are robbing colored boarding houses...

1439
02:25:09,116 --> 02:25:11,576
...and setting them on fire. From 21st:

1440
02:25:12,906 --> 02:25:15,866
The mob havejust broken open gun store and are arming.

1441
02:25:20,586 --> 02:25:23,086
- Get the nigger! Kill him! - Tear Tammany down!

1442
02:25:23,296 --> 02:25:26,466
The marshal's office is burning down. The police is of no avail.

1443
02:25:26,626 --> 02:25:27,676
Show yourself,Tweed!

1444
02:25:27,876 --> 02:25:29,586
Two colored men brought in almost dead.

1445
02:25:31,506 --> 02:25:35,056
There are more Negroes who need help. They're being attacked all over.

1446
02:25:35,266 --> 02:25:37,016
Hey! There's a $300 man. Get him!

1447
02:25:37,186 --> 02:25:40,356
Did your daddy buy you out of the Army? Can he buy me out too?

1448
02:25:41,686 --> 02:25:45,736
There's danger of mob attacking armory, corner 21st Street,Second Avenue.

1449
02:25:45,896 --> 02:25:48,106
There is about 500 stand of arms in it.

1450
02:25:54,156 --> 02:25:57,246
The line is dead! They're trying to cut all the wires!

1451
02:26:00,536 --> 02:26:03,956
From 1st: Riot at Pier 4,North River. They have killed Negroes.

1452
02:26:04,126 --> 02:26:07,126
A crowd is here and are going to destroy this station.

1453
02:26:10,086 --> 02:26:12,296
Get her bag! Get her bag!

1454
02:26:14,426 --> 02:26:15,466
From 18th Precinct:

1455
02:26:15,636 --> 02:26:20,396
The mob have attacked the armory. There is danger of firing the building.

1456
02:26:20,556 --> 02:26:23,106
All 300 police wounded or unaccounted for.

1457
02:26:23,266 --> 02:26:24,816
Find the military and send them...

1458
02:26:25,016 --> 02:26:29,316
From 20th: Send 100 men to disperse mob assailing Mayor Opdyke's house.

1459
02:26:29,486 --> 02:26:31,236
Building set on fire by the mob.

1460
02:26:34,076 --> 02:26:37,496
Barnum's American Museum on fire. Animals are escaping.

1461
02:26:37,656 --> 02:26:40,076
Let go! Let go!

1462
02:26:40,706 --> 02:26:43,326
Hush the shickster! Hold her down!

1463
02:26:55,046 --> 02:26:59,016
Gunboat Liberty and ironclad Passaic now lying off the foot of Wall Street.

1464
02:26:59,226 --> 02:27:01,186
They are ready to open fire on the mob.

1465
02:27:01,346 --> 02:27:03,766
- Very large mob going to attack Tribune office.

1466
02:27:05,186 --> 02:27:07,856
From 16th: Mob's coming down to station. We have no men.

1467
02:27:08,026 --> 02:27:11,356
- 18th: The mob is very wild. - From 16th: 7th Regiment has arrived.

1468
02:27:11,526 --> 02:27:13,656
Foot of Canal,they are on their way to Broadway.

1469
02:27:13,816 --> 02:27:15,066
Take your hands off me!

1470
02:27:15,236 --> 02:27:17,236
The mob is about 4500 strong.

1471
02:27:17,406 --> 02:27:20,496
They're going to burn down Harlem Bridge. It is to be torched.

1472
02:27:20,706 --> 02:27:23,626
- Mr. Greeley! - The rats have taken over the city!

1473
02:27:26,786 --> 02:27:30,586
From 21st: There is an attack on the colored people in Second Avenue...

1474
02:27:30,756 --> 02:27:33,966
Mob headed for the Colored Orphans Asylum. Protect the children!

1475
02:27:34,136 --> 02:27:35,886
Rioters on Seventh Avenue, 28th Street.

1476
02:27:37,306 --> 02:27:39,136
- They have killed a Negro. - Get him!

1477
02:27:39,306 --> 02:27:41,516
What do we do with captured prisoners?

1478
02:27:41,676 --> 02:27:44,596
Prisoners? Don't take any. The mob isn't taking prisoners!

1479
02:27:44,766 --> 02:27:48,226
Don't take a prisoner in until you've put the mob down!

1480
02:27:55,526 --> 02:27:59,536
Soldiers now on 38th Street. The mob will not disperse.

1481
02:27:59,736 --> 02:28:02,206
What are your orders? What are your orders?

1482
02:28:16,926 --> 02:28:21,886
- No draft! No draft! - Show them what we think of their draft!

1483
02:28:28,686 --> 02:28:30,316
- Stick together! - All right.

1484
02:28:34,446 --> 02:28:36,566
Troop,halt!

1485
02:28:37,236 --> 02:28:39,736
Present arms!

1486
02:28:45,666 --> 02:28:47,126
On your order,Vallon.

1487
02:28:49,376 --> 02:28:51,206
Hold fast,there. Hold fast,there.

1488
02:28:51,376 --> 02:28:54,216
I order you to disperse!

1489
02:28:57,466 --> 02:28:59,046
Fire!

1490
02:29:34,506 --> 02:29:36,756
Fire starboard!

1491
02:29:49,936 --> 02:29:52,766
Starboard battery,fire!

1492
02:30:02,366 --> 02:30:04,036
Come on,let's go!

1493
02:30:10,326 --> 02:30:12,496
Fire over their heads!

1494
02:30:13,376 --> 02:30:15,546
Drive them into the square!

1495
02:30:18,256 --> 02:30:20,046
Bill!

1496
02:30:27,636 --> 02:30:29,056
Fire!

1497
02:30:29,686 --> 02:30:31,146
Advance!

1498
02:30:31,936 --> 02:30:33,896
Bill!

1499
02:30:36,936 --> 02:30:38,356
I can't walk!

1500
02:30:40,146 --> 02:30:41,696
Get up!

1501
02:31:45,296 --> 02:31:46,636
Fire!

1502
02:32:14,996 --> 02:32:18,796
- Bastards! - Shang! Shang,hold off!

1503
02:32:51,156 --> 02:32:53,286
Thank God.

1504
02:32:54,246 --> 02:32:57,076
I die a true American.

1505
02:34:59,076 --> 02:35:01,666
Tomorrow morning, get our people down to the docks.

1506
02:35:02,706 --> 02:35:07,256
I want every man and woman coming off the boats given hot soup and bread.

1507
02:35:11,756 --> 02:35:15,256
We're burying a lot of votes down here tonight.

1508
02:35:32,776 --> 02:35:37,616
In the end,they put candles on the bodies so's their friends...

1509
02:35:37,786 --> 02:35:41,996
...if they had any, could know them in the dark.

1510
02:35:43,206 --> 02:35:46,626
The city did this free of charge.

1511
02:35:47,706 --> 02:35:53,716
Shang,Jimmy Spoils, Hell-Cat,McGloin and more.

1512
02:35:55,216 --> 02:35:59,676
Friend or foe, it didn't make no difference now.

1513
02:36:19,236 --> 02:36:25,166
It was four days and nights before the worst of the mob was finally put down.

1514
02:36:26,246 --> 02:36:28,916
We never knew how many New Yorkers died that week...

1515
02:36:29,086 --> 02:36:31,916
...before the city was finally delivered.

1516
02:36:33,256 --> 02:36:38,346
My father told me we was all born of blood and tribulation.

1517
02:36:39,466 --> 02:36:43,766
And so then too was our great city.

1518
02:36:46,686 --> 02:36:51,436
But for those of us what lived and died in them furious days...

1519
02:36:51,606 --> 02:36:57,066
...it was like everything we knew was mightily swept away.

1520
02:36:57,866 --> 02:37:00,986
And no matter what they did to build the city up again...

1521
02:37:03,286 --> 02:37:05,916
...for the rest of time...

1522
02:37:06,876 --> 02:37:11,166
...it would be like no one even knew we was ever here.



